[{"Name":"mini butalia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU5d99kHIVqJcJtG39peK3K7cT3mwv8nLQY4mPb-cgd2FijQIn0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love these cute pretzels with spice I tried first time I love this and thank you shruti for all the explanations you explained all the flavour very well great customer service","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2Ki5J3RlYLNGLP58ZcdfyW2l08FmJzLaSUgP_&fid=0x0:0x993dedd70e7d2c6c"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Sathiyaseelan Suhashini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCDhZwAvUF3Q8iMEpEx8TQCvKbwiXzYFJN0uOrenEt7v0wxGX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Freshly made pretzels and better to have it right away.
But of the nutella stayed on their paper packaging.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjyyV9WYlaEHv74w4HwW_e9Ho5xOVFYQWzivZc&fid=0x0:0x993dedd70e7d2c6c"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Gen X Surrey Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnz98iwXPE1DskfLpfNg-zDV5mDy1tGmvmbNcHWdRqf6q4OTmNvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Service was good, prices were ok, pretzels were alright but could've been better. I wish they had more varieties. I have a thing for soft pretzels, I travelled all the way from Surrey just for a coupe pretzels. It was the closest location. I wish they'd open one in surrey. I was disappointed by the dip. I was expecting fresh made in store dips like some pretzel stores do. Instead they give you a sealed plastic dip like they have at pizza places. There was another pretzel place in the mall as well but it looked disappointing. My plan was to try each  place but I just skipped the other one as they didn't look tasty at all. I wish they'd add more multi flavors like a pretzel covered in cheese with jalepenos and garlic. Or a pizza pretzel with pepperoni and mozza. Instead of single flavors like garlic OR parmesan OR salt OR sesame seed. It's too simple, needs layers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBY1NrPmN_Ld-TCF-OALes0wrwXkwepdRqi5SH&fid=0x0:0x993dedd70e7d2c6c"],"When":"2020-2-4"},{"Name":"Alisha thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ402s8vzFNRblUcN4rsXKLbx1vqhmiG_HM7xBYKSKNBMWk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Girl made a mistake with my order. I ordered hotdog n bites but she made regular bites. She looked at me like I was crazy. I did say I don’t mind waiting for the hotdog bites initially.  She looked very unhappy the whole time and acted as if it was my fault and it was a huge bother.  She walked around  Miserable  the whole time.
I’m giving the three stars just because I love the hotdog bites.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J-Anne Aragones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCPH5rV97kx8aqxYzAlBkfIQPpbuNDMnzSc2yBloYdIXrtWvVF=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I came back here 2 consecutive days and for some reason they are ALWAYS sold out of the pretzel dog. And most of the time they close earlier than designated closing hours. On the other note, theres a small family business downstairs called little Monk and theyre very delicious. I'd rather go there","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Whenever family comes to town, a trip to Mr Pretzels is a religion.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tammy Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn0N2I5STxk6Dw-kQhoKTxOlHlPrvcouHiB9OgzjAG84pt3M0D_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"tldr: portions are tiny, yummy food and very kind and friendly staff

Food Quality: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️5/5
The food quality is amazing. Always fresh and tasty seafood as well as vegetables. Great variety and lots of options for different diets.

Food Quantity: ⭐️
This location always gives way too tiny portions. The staff although kind and very stingy. The owner of the store is more generous with his portions but the other employees give so little.

Customer Service: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
The staff is very kind and friendly. Im always welcomed with a kind smile and the owner is extremely kind and the service probably the only reason I keep coming back.

Other pokerrito locations are more generous with their portions. Take a look at a bowl from this location VS a bowl from another location. I am always left disappointed with the amount of food I get. I would recommend dining here but only if the owner is the one preparing your bowl for you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkJUi6hDdc3Wq4BnSSkI0_5M9NUiRRkSZMr2NR&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Yue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXw2CzZ4ybY9X7CKP5IHpKnSQMkBHUBaUlQYAf_fIZN5iAVr40=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a fresh, tasty take on poke bowls! Great flavors, big portions, and friendly service. Perfect for a quick, satisfying meal. Love the build your own option.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO9ljuc67n4rW1pOxWgVYZx0L4wkBOQ4u95Hnm&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Amnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjcm2KnVvAXZsXO1Xw9a-BsRGj5-RmJ6nF12OqCF9XTomoPJ9CkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered a few poke bowls, and they were great. Lots of flavourful meat, crispy jalapenos and veggies, and rice that doesn't feel too hard or soggy. Not cheap, but not expensive either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTfCzDZtfFU9jT6pG03YY-peq-fXK8JGP12OPk&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Катя Rock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvavlaq9dRL5RPryQrxNlkxGmb54RhUmBQZfBV762O6kaU7Hg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stumbled upon this place in now it will be my favorite. everything here is clean, very tasty and responsive employees. I ordered poke and asked not to put tuna, instead they put me more other fish, even though I didn't ask for it. I was pleased with such attention. thank you ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyJd-s_klTxySq0N4Ix6f0Ukq3cXUOIt_X5A4&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Michael Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjvaQXd-mGb-IDA34I__MBYm4cIx_eMc7H7qAp6kQz09PKUA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I just ordered delivery from this location today, and my brother and I are extremely disappointed. We both built our own bowls. Mine consisted of 7 scoops of protein total, but after looking at the bowl it looks equivalent to a regular bowl with 2-3 scoops of protein. My brothers large bowl with an extra scoop of protein looks like it is equivalent to a regular sized bowl. The portions were horrendous. I paid for an extra 5 scoops of protein total between the two bowls, just to have it amount to a visual 2-3 scoops worth in each bowl. This is on top of the 3 scoops that come with the large bowl option. All other toppings seemed like they have been halved also, especially  the base rice and the kale noodles I paid extra for.
Waited for two bowls filled with half AIR.

I would give zero stars if there was an option. I hope others do not receive the same treatment when they order delivery from you, this is unacceptable. Do better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Caique Santiago","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOox6PUq5eWC3lBaLydouQ7QUD4ciNU4rnLlNGRkAI_yOtiXUG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite of the bowl places. Always fresh ingredients, their wasabi basil sauce is delicious and this location got a very friendly service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5FwuIsT-B2jAqQOywZDqhxq97l2oyre3iXbsS&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Lina C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKbsQQl1N-BQDxBgK7N8-u_lcReIeD-M7vrDyswe_xAfT6bSg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have always had great food and awesome service:)!!
We ordered Ahi tuna and it was super good.
Especially a guy who looks like the owner,
He is always so kind and nice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlvMqyCyn5njGvT19c0EAO_3HgnQdZb1mC5TbZ&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Charles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW64Ss-ojDrxP41iMg-J0WxqtXB3TGqBajw2Nh0lV6aakNiaxrs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fresh ingredients and presented well, but pricy for the amount of poke protein you get","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNP0IAlAwDml1QlQfrbD4lQQ_Slkssx4GE2Bqe4&fid=0x0:0x428ac64b2432bb89"],"When":"2024-12-19"}]

[{"Name":"Epicurean N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8F2hZFp8tNbGv13CvazOYxszMBfr74pEmTirvdqgCh1LKAg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Jeez, I’ve never dealt with service this bad. The person at the till was straight up rude and cold and just didn’t look like he wanted to entertain anyone.

Rethink if you want to go here for your coffee. You won’t be coming out of it with a smile. Service would get a 0 if possible.

Didn’t ask me what ice cream I wanted in a combo. Just assumed and proceeded.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Z Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXs-pJ1HJcJcEs9CvV5lP2Uh95o0TMQA_oMLKcGyRZlHrF1s475OA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Latte taste very very good, I like the quality! And it’s not that expensive comparing to JJ Beans or Starbucks. I’d say it’s better than Starbucks with lower price, it’s not that good comparing to JJ beans however it’s cheaper. So, definitely would rate it a five star and would recommend this place for coffee.

The baristas is very friendly and professional.

I didn’t try anything else, so I can’t speak for it. I’ll try something else next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0zVP5T8DxL8VYkDDM_WWbT3VM7B5WCQwKA1tL&fid=0x0:0xaa360e56d49a8ed"],"When":"2023-2-24"},{"Name":"Alexander Hall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjri7OlzP7_qmWMStASb8sZ2_DQ5XxCIUtfzRCuquk2Xd9TA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lavazza Coffee brings a taste of Italy to every sip. Known for their rich espresso and harmonious blends, you can expect a luxurious crema and flavors that dance on your palate. Whether it’s a bold espresso or a velvety latte, Lavazza delivers quality that’s hard to beat. With friendly service and prices that make sense, it’s a coffee experience that’s definitely worth the buzz. A five-star choice for any coffee enthusiast!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brankica Celic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9s5qdqFzmm5T8Omt29hy_F8KRwPoOeitvHEgVetwULYKJbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The store hours are the same as the mall hours. I understand everyone wants to go home, but you dont refuse a paying customer. It was one of those treats i really enjoyed when I visit the mall, but makes me just want to boycott and never buy from there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Volodymyr Voitenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYqnN-2JKFa9ZSRNs0SgbCTf95vdyy1C629X3emaDkU3Wsr3Dx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"this is not your defeated starbucks.   nostalgia for Europe, exquisite coffee with delicious tiramisu","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julie Roberts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnhnH9M-NuS_BvlXhfhiuNR1PVRscfSXvhOIOuhk0HDR_cg1U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lavazza Coffee is a delightful and aromatic coffee brand that never fails to satisfy my morning caffeine cravings. [{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Philly cheese steak made to order. I got the original which was $13+ tax. Bread was really nice and soft and meat had a lot of flavour. The size was not very big - about a regular hot dog style bun. Overall, it was just ok and I almost couldn’t tell there was cheese in the sandwich. Bit overpriced and  it’s mostly a self serve seating area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9TA8eFmuPWUYAvkHq66yxl3eD8K1ym9FQTvPH&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Hsien Chih Shu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXT32DrVfiGKIMJsboF0f2_bKM3-NM-TxMQgT4fouAzt1CWeKcL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the lobster shrimp one, the taste was great, the bun was crispy, and there were some veggies wrapped in the bread underneath the cheese. If not the price I’d visit more often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMwFUvjuPx4dokAoVPbeEGS9JljLxGK-3N9YcR&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Kym Manubag","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWARl0-96yyT7QuwxuiVCkWgWId5Aj6lYFjDUo7YF4M6NmNOECP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good!! Very underrated restaurant. Definitely try the ACC fries 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrFFFeA5ner-ey1DYpZ0BE_5Xse2kUY3lUp9qI&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2024-11-7"},{"Name":"Harshit Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmG6gEgJpRvIOCqifAN4_INZ-2ntkQ1xNMdKJ9WVMUPHSfjtzlyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Located on the 2nd floor, right under Cineplex and close to Winners store.
I bumped into this cozy little place a few days ago. I tried their bestsellers, The New Yorker & The Cowboy. Both were super yummy. The meat was juicy, just the right temperature and the sauce was, ohhhhh, so good!!
The quantity is a bang-for-the-buck. They even have a good seating area, sufficient for at least 10 folks. The music adds to the chill ambience of the place. The attendants were extremely courteous.
Must try for meat lovers. I am definitely coming back for sure. Highly recommended!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf3cWZ4wS4AgFCbYgaBBHeUKHIWkMvqoweDwfl&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2022-7-18"},{"Name":"Erica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiBiehVBMqDRcQQk3J28lEnqLVQ-p5tIOA0Zlj3wvs65IUmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Located right below Metropolis at Metrotown mall's Cineplex theatre (by the stairs). Only 2 tables open for dine-in, but feel free to order take-out or delivery.

My order:

-Japanese Style Cheesesteak: my personal favourite - juicy sautéed mushrooms & onions, aged cheddar, wasabi mayo and of course premium ribeye steak slices. It’s saucy, and the cheese blend enhances the flavour.
-Koagie (Korean Hoagie): Kimchi was good (not too sour or spicy), so I could comfortably eat it.
-New Yorker: the classic if you don't want to venture away from a
"normal Philly cheesesteak" - topped with fresh tomatoes and lettuce

Overall, the hoagie roll was soft on the inside, and a good chewy texture on the outside. I reheated mines in the microwave, and it still tasted good several hours later. These cheeseteaks are more saucy than the traditional cheesesteaks, which I personally enjoyed as every bite was filled with flavour. Very filling - best to share if you want to try different flavours. I also really liked their assortment of cheeses (no fake Cheez-Whiz stuff, sorry if you like that though), I think they use aged cheddar, provolone, and some others in a cheese blend. They definitely don't cheap out, and use a generous portion of tender/sliced prime rib steak. All cheesesteaks are made-to-order on a grill when you place your order.

-Onion Rings: skinny-style
-Deep Fried Pickles: good thick cut of pickles to breading ratio
-ACC Fries (Garlic Butter & Parmesan): classic thick cut fries with a very "potato-y" flavour
-White Chocolate Blueberry Milkshake: quite sweet, definitely for people that have a sweet tooth

Also, I definitely have to mention the house-made sauces, they're so good for dipping the onion rings, pickles, and fries (cheesesteaks were saucy enough, so I didn't need it there). My personal favourites were the roasted garlic aioli, smoke Chipotle BBQ (not to overpowering or salty), and mustard (real mustard seeds).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy4x4SxlJVE85YyYd_JGDKxnrGdZkXh6kVcPFk&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2021-3-11"},{"Name":"Dimitri Pelosof","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfM58KLNF27k8gTDOAVxOk2C6YwnGFyNuoc3mVfuH_B24uvA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big shot was so amazing the staff member truffle aioli sauce is bomb would definitely come back again best cheesesteak I ever had.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOB1N550TcmKkU4hbjaA_E1bPslT_EyeIYt90u&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"tarneema propa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwd9dHiU9egWWKWk0jQDOep6xbwkVQ_SHmBqvP7L114SCcbxlJ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Recently the poutine which I always order from here is  not up to the standard. The quantity is less and the fries aren’t crispy like before. I do not remember her name but whenever my order is made by one Asian girl the order is perfect . However, unfortunately whenever the male worker makes it I always get disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered a few cheesesteaks and the ACC fries to-go. Service was efficient, but it wasn't busy. The fries were crispy but standard, they could have been more fragrant with the garlic butter. The sandwiches were the star. I liked them all (Korean Hoagie, Lobster Shrimp, Japanese Style), but my favourite was the Japanese Style. It had a great umami flavour.

Both that one and the Koagie had plenty of filling, the seafood had significantly less (but I expected that) - good dill flavour, though. I'd skip the sides, but will definitely be back for the innovative cheesesteaks!

Edit: After seeing the company's Instagram story and other photos, I realize that they were running a free caviar promotion on the lobster shrimp melt. The staff forgot to give it for our order (which was done directly at the shop) so that was unfortunate. The owner reached out on Instagram though, so appreciate them correcting the lapse for next time around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBjMvBS50qN9T-bpCuZ4cr-D64q1x4KynmAjBo&fid=0x0:0xac3531c6b4a6f4ed"],"When":"2021-1-30"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Quinn L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6vx0ezJG0GDaJFb7qHXLdrAbL4LGTjhR-05HfHlbp5QPFSkU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My parents and I dined at Earls Station Square for my birthday. Laren was our sever for the evening and he was great until an order mix up which put a damper on the rest of our time at Earls.

I ordered the Cajun Blackened Chicken but instead was served a salmon dish. When I informed Laren about the wrong order, I was met with doubt and annoyance. Laren did not offer to correct the mistake right away and it seemed he wanted to persuade me to keep the salmon. At no point did Laren show accountability for his mistake nor did he apologize for it, it almost appeared that he casted blame my way like I misremembered what I ordered. I had deliberated between a burger and the Cajun Blackened Chicken when I reviewed the menu, not once did I even consider the salmon. I honestly felt gaslit by Laren during this whole interaction… I was certain I ordered the chicken…

Unfortunately I was not able to share a proper meal with my family on my birthday. By the time the correct dish was served, my parents were already finished with their food. What was supposed to be a joyous occasion was shadowed by Laren’s poor attitude and the awkward atmosphere that followed the conversation about the mix up. I felt it was obvious he avoided our table the rest of the evening while he was attentive to others around us. We also waited quite a while for our bill, which furthered the frustration.

The food somewhat compensated for the poor customer service. All of our dishes were delicious and well made. In addition, I was pleasantly surprised by the complimentary brownie at the end of our meal (not the birthday dessert special, which I felt too awkward to ask Laren about).

Although the food was very appetizing, it’s really a shame that Laren’s sour attitude and lack of professionalism made our dining experience uncomfortable and subpar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPl0b02dlIbOIgXLcQPnM_0BPk9NI9LzdhBP2nz&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Thais Oliveira","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXD1ghyGnpuIJs3_L2s_WmL-t8i8bpNdTnvYmAiDTd_aiIWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was the best dining experience I’ve ever had. I chose Earls to celebrate my birthday with my friends (20 people in total), and the service was exceptional!
I got a hand-written birthday card from the hostess as soon as I arrived, the manager checked in with us multiple times, and the servers did an excellent job managing all of the orders!
I wasn’t expecting so much care and attention to detail, the customer service went above and beyond to provide such an amazing experience. Thank you so much for making my day so special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOYcWsoJ4Sg-c5WIHTObN6rqg38usDOhOcKtVb&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Absolutely one of the worst steaks I’ve ever had, it was chewy, and dry even though I asked for medium rare. It felt like it was half frozen when it was cooked, but likely it’s because the quality of meat there is garbage and I had to send it back to the kitchen for a different dish. I am typically not the type of person to send food back, so the meat would’ve been unacceptable. Would not be going back. On another note, their pizza was not bad. The crust was very thing and cooked well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN19wS9BSgfoO40VY-Ws8wo0Fz0NqXKpgRtfJ1B&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Here is our favorite bar for gathering together. We always go here for happy hour from 2 to 5 PM. One of the waiters here, named Miguel, is really friendly and patient. Try this place once, you won't regret it.

Don't miss the key lime pie dessert, and the guava strawberry drink is really delicious too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2ebYlyIx8eMGJekE8Rq9BW0TH9xCMdakeYVG3&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I always prefer Earl’s over other restaurant chains in Canada as it delivers consistent food quality.

The Poke bowl, pasta and Cobb salad we ordered today was good.

Staff were friendly and efficient even though i think they are a little bit understaffed, which is understandable in today’s poor economy.

The oyster was disappointing though.  It was
the thinnest, the most tasteless oyster i have ever ordered in my life time.  I don’t think it should be served if the kitchen care enough.

Not a bad meal

Card machine: preset 18%, 20%, 22% tips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3aJIuyevPgeA_g4YhwHuCyuQICJVC8NpIxcVa&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Ivan Ruano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlD88eOgp4LoyjUgNEvZilCX7_nfJHbEXsoz58oEF29KOX8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Celebratory dinner with my co-workers/friends.
- Elegant, modern décor, serene ambiance
- Staff & service was friendly, well-trained, & efficient
- Exquisite flavours, made from seasonal and high-quality ingredients
Our server was Cedric & Ayla. They were lovely, friendly and well trained.
Highly recommend for special occasions!
10/10","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCFzPBfJmggXxXwcI-OMuxvs0Za3hI0UY689Ng&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Leanna Wen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVsfJTW-TsAXmUcndj_rCxFGk2NAIqCPLdhOtY5q_4RrmYAlg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great time coming here with my friends for a celebratory dinner during happy hour! The staff, Cedric and Ayla, were super kind and friendly. The food was delicious and the service was quick! Would recommend coming here with your friends and family!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2qGIlUQvWzIaKr56NGZVESw2pAAMRsnMg6fw&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Jason Tribbiani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXpvlAY0NULhaj1b4k1yZZtRXFlzsqxg5gIO8-kzQ1-Qy-iq7d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"**Rating: 4.5/5**

We visited this Earls for a friends’ lunch gathering, and it didn’t disappoint. The atmosphere was excellent, and the food was top-notch. The staff were all very friendly, and the table service was quick and efficient. We thoroughly enjoyed our lunch and will definitely be back. Hopefully, in the near future, they’ll consider adding a kids' menu with options like mac & cheese or mini burgers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkEMQ0gFowYzqFs67zegyAiI_xkcDXq1E5n1cQ&fid=0x0:0x1e8568236be22147"],"When":"2023-12-28"}]

[{"Name":"Regina Gentile","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvbaxG6uArU-PM1ZGsBsjSohnDAFHUHmQJ_GJd3YgBGG5EQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had a matcha latte with oat milk and my boyfriend took a caramel macchiato...they were horrible:the milk was steamed really bad.
The brownie that I bought was good but even if I said that I wanted eat in the bar they served me it still in the plastic wrap...and it had a strange white spot on the surface angle...
Despite it all the girl was kind, polite and smiley, and the place was cute.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVHL4bGyLXxUBOfGlFb5N33O4kgltpB_yNTknm&fid=0x0:0xedceefa29ec83173"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Vanessa 貞懿 Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVe4T1KMOhwE494taZRZMpbzjetStEqI_naIm69hoyO07onQrJ1bA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"nice location inside metrotown mall , opposite of winners . service is good . seats got full quickly during busy time. I order a small coffee with oak milk.  Unlike starbucks, Blenze does't charge extra for non dairy milk, which is why I am leaving starbucks ! It is not a cafe if you cannot seat and relax into the aroma of your caffine !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alice TY K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjh-1n-LifIIturHdxk5ABZSWriZjpq2DRCMyp4k_fnyalglYJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"(Update added after BLENZ provided a minor response - scroll down past the line!)

In summary: my drink tasted great but overall impression… I’d spend my money elsewhere.

In detail:
Just stopped in to do some quick work with an accompaniment of a beverage (Honey Oat Hojicha) and to my utter horror and discovery as I was about to pack up, I found a trail of mouse poop and mouse pee along the back seating areas.

I took pictures of my seating area and even zoomed in to make sure I wasn’t mistaking these with sesame seeds…then I brought this up to the girl (Asian in her early 20s wearing glasses) — I had originally asked to speak to a manager but clearly this place is not on the up and up.

This girl… heard me out and she just brushed me off by saying “ya it’s beyond my pay grade and it’s not something we can avoid”.

Listen, I get it, working in the food industry.. especially in THIS mall location (Metrotown) it is something inevitable but as a business is servicing people/consumers with FOOD AND BEVERAGES. Do not lie to my face and say you clean the floors everyday. You can’t lie and say that this amount is accumulated in one single day.

Best course of action is to make sure floors are done both before opening AND after closing…
Please clean the floors… seriously.

This is a food service business not to mention a business franchise. Fraser Health have already been notified about this.

——————
Update 10/16:
Addressing the response received from BLENZ management - it is understandable that being in a mall with a pest issue is inevitable but the responses from that one employee (female, young Asian with glasses) is extremely offsetting and off brand. Overnight accumulation of rodent droppings is something you cannot prevent, I won’t deny that! However if this was something you have already been aware of and not actively trying to do more cleaning makes it very unappealing to consumers who drop in to purchase FOOD and DRINKS. These aren’t products that you can “clean” and “sanitize” after purchase before use.. these are products purchased to be consumed before they go bad.

Again, I know what a single night of rodent droppings accumulation looks like, it is definitely not what I saw and photographed. If cleaning was maintained twice a day, daily.. there wouldn’t be 1 speck visible during operating hours. This tells me and shows me that your staff is not fully and diligently cleaning in the evening as well as not thoughtfully going along the floorboards (if you know rodent activity, which clearly you do not…they tend to scale the walls and leave feces/urine along that trail).

For someone that has dealt with rodent issues both at work and at home for the last decade, please do not brush me off as if I do not know what I am talking about.

Food service businesses need to be extremely diligent and not slacking in any aspects.. this can lead to so much with food borne illnesses etc. oh and yes, Fraser Health was indeed notified and will be having follow ups with them hopefully soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU7rgPN2OuE1dwe_JaIhuzvnlxi8uY2ZBeO8vX&fid=0x0:0xedceefa29ec83173"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Mich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUk4SJkfT35Lr0ZUsPgvMr5zk32J8m9TBN0sQWcp7LTonWmgO0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Prices have definitely skyrocketed, sadly. Mocha went from $4 ish to now $7. Quality is subpar, would’ve been fine if the quality went up too. Anyways that was probably my last visit to the store","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Gastrocritic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyj2QSdE_6jR0qvZQfzny8fYu8cF6Yj6STWgJFcDB_QUHNaYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"What a waste. LavAzza should hv banned this cafe for using its coffee brand to bring in the unknowing fans like me. I've been a follower of LavAssa for years. I like their aroma, the texture & non acidic taste. This cafe made it taste like water. Their coffees are lighter than Tims. The baristas there aren't even coffee drinkers. Don't be fooled.

Update to the Owner
The coffee beans were not the issue, it's how your staff made the coffee that had spoiled my experience. My observations indicated that your staff were either untrained in how to make a proper cup of coffee OR they just didn't seem to care. You as the owner should try your coffees as a mystery shopper to better assess your coffee standard. Good luck!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmc_fPkuKOFRm9zZQT_5pnOqoYuLEJJ-BE5E-M&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time trying their gelato. We're allowed to taste test a maximum of 3 flavours. We found flavours like Black Sesame and Kulfi to be very strong, more enhanced than a lot of ice cream we've had before (which is a good thing). However, I settled on Cashew Dark Cherry (roasted cashew butter) and Pistachio. The cup is fairly small, but the server did do their best to pack in the gelato. The gelato has a nice creamy texture, which we enjoyed. Their only vegan options are sorbetto, but they do have a number of gelato flavours that are gluten free. Popular outlet in the middle of the hallway in the upper level of Metrotown. It was busy, and I imagine it will be even more popular in the summer!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1qmjim6_wxMCjP0tBqepcv5DIZblqqYIwJFiW&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2024-4-25"},{"Name":"Fuzzy Nemo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhjGNDhI-RZYgIiVRXnRDEQCiyyP-dsVjb7EhBkcymNr9MvYi0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have tried a few gelato places in the past,  and I have read great reviews for this place, it was a great disappointment.   The service was quite slow and quite poor, but I had ordered one scoop in a cone and my gelato was smeared onto the side of my cone and a dollop on top.   So I basically got a hollow ice cream cone with,  what looked to a scoop of ice cream that covered the top of my cone.   Where as the next person that ordered one scoop on a cup,  actually had a full scoop.  I thought it was a rip off.  Gelato was not outstanding, so I think they are pretty overrated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSN9YoTnkLi0RWhinL4Dj_c6saZUOGj0sgJxdU&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Farid Entezari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV35QQyx2JmA30yOGa4kCXMTDZjBP0mMYjKzM0CL9HNh-FF7LAEEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My visit to Bella Gelateria in Metrotown Burnaby was a delightful surprise! While I had reservations about the Akbar Mashti Zafran ice cream, it turned out to be incredibly delicious. The flavor exceeded my expectations, and the generous portion size was impressive. I was pleasantly surprised, and if I could, I would give this gelateria a perfect 10-star review. Bella Gelateria truly knows how to create an exceptional ice cream experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZ2aZi7p21F6Y2rXjTMsm1uRhbrX7TzHw7OnjY&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2023-10-6"},{"Name":"Hans-Joachim Stark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJj1UGaFPSbp-uwFeIaWaDyh55eeuEMOT-LhJaFwrh1tUU1WQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today ordered the affogato at their Metrotown outlet tempted by the nice advertised product pic:
Two large icecream balls in a bath of coffee served in a beautiful tulip shaped glass.
The reality what we got:
1 icecream ball (instead of 2 on the pic) in a paper cup with a wooden spoon and the coffee came to daylight after starting to eat the icecream.
Price tag $9.45.
Beautiful shop counter though, but I would expect the reality mirroring the advertised product.
Unhappy afternoon break.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdh1twcnWNfURVod_IZoz0JwazSZSQuiPoS_w3&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got to try their gelato during the free birthday treat. I got the black sesame and wow! It was so delicious. I had black sesame ice cream once in Japan a while back and I could not find something as good as it here in greater vancouver. So many places have gritty ones and some have overly nutty flavors. This one was perfect and I would definitely come here to eat it again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPC58Y0Qhyf1z7qgS5ew3fFOry90RKC16oUtru&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Katherine Al Nouisser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUX8PPcPtAcITIPNoa2OW_FNthNqbXlws8hwfrn1eWr2XimJJjY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They do not care about customer satisfaction at all. The person that took my mother and I’s order seemed new and there was a bit of a language barrier but we understand and were patient and nice towards her regardless. She was a sweet woman and even confirmed our order with us a couple of times.

I ordered the iced matcha latte and my mother ordered the regular caramel macchiato. The new hire got it mixed up and thought I’d ordered the regular (hot) matcha latte and my mother the cold macchiato. I work in customer service and feel for employees, therefore I politely told them that I ordered the iced latte and patiently waited. This other blond girl that was working, quickly made the right order and handed it to us. Though, I’m not exactly sure what happened but I think the blond girl might’ve scolded the new employee because after we told her it was the wrong order, they conversed and the new employee started crying.

My mother’s macchiato was good. My drink on the other hand was not pleasant at all. At first I thought it was just because it was unsweetened so I asked for a sugar packet and I mixed it in. It was still horrible. It was extremely grainy and I’ve had matcha numerous times before and it was never like this. I even poured the matcha in the sink and there was an insane amount of leftover powder. Matcha, if made right, is not supposed to be grainy at all.

After tasting the matcha the second time I went back. I did not think to go back, I was willing to let it be, but my mother insisted because after all, we did spend our money on it. I politely let the blond girl know that the matcha was extremely grainy and that I could not continue to drink it as it was bothering my throat. I even apologized for coming back because I didn’t want to make their day any harder, and it would’ve been fine had the blond girl not been passive aggressive and rude about it. She claimed that that was the “right way to make matcha” (it’s not) and said that she won’t do anything about the order because she did nothing wrong she only “made it the right way”. I did not expect to get a refund or even a remake but simple accountability and apology would’ve sufficed.

Keep in mind, I was making sure that I was not being rude, even with my tone or my wording. Her reaction was completely unprofessional and disrespectful. That was horrible customer service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J. Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKd1bXGF7n1AcDiiPqdWfNDpJyzpJv3KZmlbswN2U0AYmbvkQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a big fan of Bella Gelateria, i am glad that they opened one at Metrotown! Friendly staff, even offering me to take some samples prior to order. My girl got a free b-day gellato just for signing up!
Yuju is a must try! So refreshing! Love every bite! 💓","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPn7h5O_aEfIRouKDco7U-DoyapmNK2JTDlxy64&fid=0x0:0xf2940e68ab5b931"],"When":"2022-5-17"}]

Although it's not a very big place,  they have quite a few baristas and exceptionally quick.  Although there was a long line up,  they went through it very quickly.   I decided to do a mobile order,  when I saw the long line up and it was extremely fast as well.  Kudos to them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"K Day","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEZTlctZ7GsbqTa1Fl-OAw34HHUYyIBEANb8cTbXC7ELWIjJXADg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Located in a grocery store, I wasn't expecting much other than the basic drinks.
The 1st few days of our stay (@ the hotel across the street) were pretty good. A shorter lady with long brown hair was the barista. She took and made orders quickly and was friendly. Her drinks tasted good, like other Starbucks and she was thoughtful.
The last 2 days the barista has been a tall thin girl. Can't remember her name but it starts with an M. She's nice enough but so unsanitary. She handles the money then goes straight to making the drinks. She puts her entire thumb inside the silver pitcher the milk goes into for frothing, instead of holding it by the handle. She also grabs all of the cups and lids by the top smearing whatever is on her hands directly on the cups and lids. Oh and the drinks she makes are so bad. Today's Frap isn't even blended. There are big white patches in the drink where it wasn't blended. It's all supposed to be brown...
Overall it seems like it's hit or miss here, depending on which barista you get b/c there is only ever 1.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ricardo Cordero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnKuquOzPvw3TLmnC6oDZ-xmaF2sPw050glZZe1yWDH6smLw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Got this hot chocolate that was very smelly and tasted very bad and not even after 15 minutes when I arrived home I opened the lid and found some gross mold things on it, 100% would not recommend","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKKSQ6spBco27FeFSaPqAfPOdyHYJhLwayS-oY&fid=0x0:0x9f4debb7713a672"],"When":"2022-1-29"},{"Name":"Jimmy Toungate","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZ4JglMqepw_UddqbsHZbowmE0Y0dQvBBqs1YEDYEhKHfKIMcS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service and coffee. I ordered my Mexican Mocha which is a mocha with cinnamon steamed into it. Earlier in the day had been to Tim Horton's and tried to order the same and the lady looked at me like I was from another planet. I'll just stick to Starbucks when traveling in Canada!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kevin (KC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrZpzDcm4xbgvb_oOynyP_bQvwIe7l-wMoPIs8L4UeVZ-waBkO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great Korean Dessert Spot!

The portions were pretty big. We ordered 3 shaved ice bowls and it was more than enough to feed 6 people.

We ordered 3 shaved ice bowls:
- cheesecake
- strawberry
- injeolmi (signature bowl)

All of them tasted great. The interior was spacious and cozy and there was plenty of parking in the area.

Overall, I would recommend this place for Korean shaved ice desserts if you’re in the area! 🙂🍧","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYpON4e7oIzSI_GZHejvPpWPIActnfFvRiXAKP&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Jessy J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHNRFw0Z_JgaU0TxGr1Pv5X-w9V6JzR0bnCuTDlGr_7pfsbx_k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time here on a weekend afternoon. Line up was acceptable. Looked like a little short on front staff and there’s always an extra few minutes wait between each customer to take their orders.

Wait time was about 10-12 min after we ordered. The taiyaki was small but quite tasty with the whipped cream. The Oreo bingsoo was great too but I agree with some previous comments that the ice was lacking flavour.

All in all it’s a neat place for desserts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9ak1wymaGA3-MRY1Jn6NwPuo2xE00KkSS426&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The fresh fruits served at Sulbing Café are delicious! Beautifully ripe, sweet and the perfect accompaniment to their bingsu.

It's hard to pick a flavour, but you really can't go wrong. Mango is my favourite, and strawberry is a very close second. But be forewarned: it's a seasonal fruit. So if you visit in the winter, it's unlikely to be available.

If you like cheesecake, definitely add the cheese! It's not too sweet, and it's a delicious addition to the mango bingsu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWgs_C9z9LK8tFbv7kxrtHw4LSOYd5yEsb3raL&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Kim L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrsm9uWsgDlJo9sBOfcAbnWwOOYhj1ksL8fCyKWa_9jtKX9dlsTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I ordered Green Tea Bingsu. It looked pretty good but the tastes bland… it comes with red bean rice cake it tastes like bit old.. not soft at all. It was my first time visiting here will be no next time…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgvJiJebs6du7w2De1RW9h07Mo4KtvczYa5WC6&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This dessert cafe in Burnaby was ok. I enjoyed a mango cheese ice when I visited. I have visited other dessert cafes that seemed friendlier and more comfortable. I didn't notice the tables or floors being cleaned often. Overpriced for what I had but a fun find but I probably won't visit again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTROJj0vm1hPNIvHp1cmM3_PDO_i5sfxBhgRpn&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Cyrus Yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwd8GV9_xN2UT6DSuLVl33bJJc7mzj0UQ6J-1qGzgv0MySHfc_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Bingsu is one my favourite varieties of shaved ice and Sulbing Cafe is one of my favourite places to get bingsu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOriyHkc9Q3JUOQijvzZaOx3nlCzJDwqbIkzJH8&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Angela Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmoYI5U5PkD3slb8KXj4_eunuAJ0OQg5lHarEbqHy5ARzTjtmN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Waffle was good. Friends ordered matcha shaved ice which tasted good and surprisingly not too sweet. There was no customer service there. All you have to do is order on the kiosk, wait to be called by your number, and then pick up your foods.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfxB-yhldWofff1_WrBUx8URQtYHGWlbaaZAq6&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2024-7-23"},{"Name":"Sweets Fanatic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKT4q9vq4bFnKURKLo-IuFZkNgSUZrYyHCHwVq7PvVTaTofHHc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful, stunning, exactly as the showcase's appearance.

I ordered the green tea ice cream and it was better than the ones I had in Richmond. Though my friend ordered the chocolate brownie one and I thought that it was better than the green tea. The green tea didn't have much of a matcha or green tea taste, as it was covered in chocolate powder. But the brownies on the side were absolutely delicious. My friend's had cheese and whipping cream and I am surprised that they went so well together.

Have to say, the appearance is very instagramable.

Taste: 4/5
Price: ~20$
Washroom: very clean, very girl friendly.

Come back rate: 80%","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO03_I_IvxkDQNmVozB1jnypN7RmBy0U-iht0Xg&fid=0x0:0xcc03184564a52bb"],"When":"2023-5-9"}]

[{"Name":"Christy Pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVeIPsvPzIaRm1ZE0QnnatpMuvcZwUrSxAsYFNh5_0AwON1A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Got the strawberry croissant, injeolmi muffin, and chocolate cake. Food was good but nothing really stood out in terms of flavor. All pastries are freshly baked, and flavor was not overly sweet which is good. Croissant was light, crispy, and airy. Chocolate cake was average. Very limited parking and seating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGIxLVhwqSTEcwp4lj2Oy-3tnJn71Glu8nwpa-&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Benedict Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6PoqDB0s0FZ-wOoleDfCsv0mfJt9Lh41GYqE5v8-k2M8tAauT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee and Pastries were amazing like their Jubilee location. We ordered their Vanilla Latte and it has a good balance of the strength of the coffee and the sweetness of the vanilla. The coffee bun is one of the best I've tried and the croissant was good too. Not a lot of seating and there were barely inside. Seatings are mostly outside which was not too bad. This place is mostly takeaway and I understand as it is behind the Royal Oak Skytrain Station.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvQKppyVZr6wbFxSz2wHjtjUKF2M6ZGOvodndw&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Yumyum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2Ps7OMRb5Woekeu-WRhO2P9H6MQ739yHSEC9SvN4CQ52rgx4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"La Foret is always my go to place for cakes/sweet treats when there are events, birthdays or other special celebrations.

This year I want to give it a try and I ordered the “Berry Christmas Tree” (Strawberry Cream Cake) cake for Christmas. I placed my order on their website, everything went well. Since they’re closed on the 25th, the only option is to pick up the cake the day before, and I did! Picking the cake up on 24th ard 11am, pick up was easy, everything went well, we quickly put the cake in the fridge after we got home.

Buttt!!!!!!!  Yes there’s a but. When I open the cake on 25th at night, the colours from “Merry Christmas” faded and the red went on the white cream, and it looks really bad…..  ok, then when we cut it up, first bit was super sweet, then you can see those sponge cake and the creams are already falling apart.

I understand it’s a busy holiday season and I can accept the fact that these cakes are made in centralized kitchen, I get that. But it’s one of the worst cake I’ve ever eaten.  No more cakes from La Foret.

Anywayyy, Merry Christmas to you all, hope you have a wonderful holiday and not to have eaten something like this during such festive time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmMw6EiKjqOdBb-8wosPlifz7W3HDZlTO7qPdm&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-12-26"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food here is just as good as the other Burnaby location. This spot is super convenient via the skytrain but a lot smaller. There is very limited seating indoors and isn’t suitable for large groups but there is outdoor patio seating. Decor and atmosphere is great though. We went close to closing time so not a large selection but we enjoyed our blueberry cake and matcha tiramisu. Also cool to see they sell ice cream too, would like to try the injeolmi flavour!

Would come to pick up pastries but not to hang out. Parking is plenty and free too, in a dead end street so not busy.

The individual piece take out cake box is really cute, our piece fell over though so it needs to be better secured.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfNjBPc5M43PEiVaputpY-_e2MvXlMu3aDToGO&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Liza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU6psZuYm5issGPqVIywDJmiQmgvYke0cz4aCVVktU9NoaykdJkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a smaller branch compared to the main one. They also serve drinks, bakery and sweet items, as well as sandwiches. Their salmon sandwich is particularly delicious! This place is perfect for a quick bite on the go. During the warm season, it's also nice to sit outside. I would highly recommend this place for a quick coffee or tea break, especially compared to their main branch where waiting times can be very long during peak hours. It's a great solution for a short visit. Strongly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfYB3LVjo0WmnfhE9qqM8-juqEe4KoHK9Xg_F5&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-3-24"},{"Name":"Subrata Chakrabarti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5RDAw8Aem70tR9tIzdz9rELiNgtIPePCYMQ2ARfSBfQvG1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here, couple of weeks ago.  They have lots of choices for an indulgence with coffee or tea.  It is a small cafe.

Seating was on the outside front patio. Nothing in the restaurant. That means eat/ drink standing if you don’t want to be in the sun.

We hade cheese cake. It was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm9rODDgseemd2r_Ftth6ZZTbcc6xWqgLJqA0i&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Jessica Dhaliwal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOeC5VCbc6g3HH3dxXpDS9bE993HEKMDVI3SjHX2aNdHbQOJHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Omg the pineapple cloud croissant totally made my day today after I was having tummy troubles it actually helped and was amazingly delicious.  Squid ink matcha cruffin to die for. Seems to be a better shape than the round croissants too","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0jue-ZZ7DOK6kYd5c31Yf3GaKRD8utNwalUxO&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A great place to chill out with friends & family. Nice airy ambience.

There was no one enforcing the seating limit.
We ordered drinks and desserts. I had the strawberry croissant which was 3/5. Fresh croissant with some strawberry slices and whipping cream. Lacked the wow factor. The other desserts were well liked.

Parking’s a challenge even though there’s parking in the back.

They have breakfast, lunch and dinner choices. Items are on the pricey side.

Hours are 8 am - 10 pm from M-F. 9 am - 10 pm on Sat & Sun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPk647oMM5DgGIemvBduTQnnvYjTB1ERTOVduHG&fid=0x0:0x3da6ce7c41453574"],"When":"2023-8-27"}]

[{"Name":"Cole Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOU6XCX3s_R0vWndse-P-J59JZDVGZbi6kfyG2pJARhX4qsYzZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly staff, good drinks, quick service.

Their dragonfruit lemonade was quite enjoyable with the slightly frozen dragonfruit chunks. Although, you can't really sip it in through the tiny opening slot.

The other white chocolate cold brew latte was fantastic. Smooth to drink, sweet but not to a diabetic level.

Overall the environment is nice and there's bathrooms upstairs too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0h6I_cew-gfOb4_o2h2s639_CmtNVrSN_AnOR&fid=0x0:0xefea695ec1f18ed9"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Chris F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5iETqIQBeQI1auEFM0Tc1cLHlBlPg-u_xQZRZgDTvUjh6noO8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good location. Good hours. What you’d expect.  Friendly service.  First time anyone has offered to hear my banana loaf at a Starbucks.  That was nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPWz38AawuOX_lWq-sZMwI7FMut1d95_Nrl_6B&fid=0x0:0xefea695ec1f18ed9"],"When":"2022-9-21"},{"Name":"Cathy Knowlton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjKNfxetA-6Nc7Skaku2fo8PLxnVOgSXPafePlBXxx0r-3Alau=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Arrived at 5:30, asked for a sandwich and was denied as was told they were “closing”. It closes at 6. Person after me was served. Maybe they didn’t want to take 2 minutes to heat up a sandwich","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mario Salimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-p4s_ESIV3psypg07TJ-l6iZnZ4tkbky6IGl9Bj-vfdqhsgzv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We arrived 20 minutes before they usually close on Sundays and we were informed that they closed early because they ran out of their stock. The barista however was nice  enough to offer a free coffee since the till was closed. Starbucks employees sometimes go far and beyond to make sure customers" satisfaction is met. That is appreciated. Thank you","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"EMIFA IMMIGRATION","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6kj4ds5jPT16AwZjfIhgd1B3NLj1QsppV-n43lL-TjXQP_90=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very approachable staff. My friend had a birthday and they were very nice and passing him a gift. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Chen (夜典)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzZq9uhq2vR2lG0v1l69cksc_phCGJ-0ErvXA73ElRNLWWuN4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Always closed when I needed it the most. The only time I've managed to catch it when it's open is always when I'm getting off work and heading home to get some sleep. As a result this Starbucks is never there for me. I have only one question for the owner/manager of this location. Why is this Starbucks operating hour so short when it's right next to a 24 hour casino? couldn't this location stay open till 10pm or 12pm at least?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Babak khonsari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOTO13jFuI1-Kg2krvc-IaNUcnjjLBkHnuzyAZXHulvsaZLyZiVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Perfect quiet location. Lots of seats and free internet of course. Good friendly staff. I actually got some work done. Not so many distractions. In a hot day, in a spacious air conditioned Hotel lobby.  Perfect","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Francis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgfmbUHLwmxF3ATfQGv1RD5eZck6TDnyYt1IZAHB6YDFw4kfEYkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pros: Convenient location with nice sofas to lounge on.
Cons: It's a franchise Starbucks so you can't just "scan" and can't collect points with promotions.
Bottom Line: Starbucks inside the casino and hotel. So it's a nice environment to do some reading or relaxing.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Sybil Bulut","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5A17qbTOh87CsQkJ0JpYXp0UdKzDGKtjXgWwMdyUlUNGY-wA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I’m paying $15 for TWO venti coffees, I EXPECT TWO venti coffees, both $7 drinks are only 2/3 full. I wouldn’t be upset if it was like an inch from the rim because that’s reasonable, but this is super unacceptable. We hadn’t even drank from them yet- we could feel they were extremely light so we wanted to open them up first.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJcmTBKWAhOmug8PW6-cJRiKlk3AKGc9ENj0IX&fid=0x0:0x4348892232f8aef8"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Karen Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXchMPPAN3zqOoag_ixABnvIJMH6A1alhdVdwJdZOdnJvvZotnpUg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Grabbed a coffee because my friend was running late. My Barista Shela was exceptional. She was patient and gave me a recommendation to my existing order and it was super yummy!

The reception at this location was a bit wonky so I had a bit of a challenge in getting in to my app. She suggested me to use the public wifi!

Thank you Shela! You were amazing 🙆🏻‍♀️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2czJdCeh7Bg8uzG1gnb4KQG70A0BpIjodQ25E&fid=0x0:0x4348892232f8aef8"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Thomas Peake (MynameisTommy)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxMJkxu3ap6jMjdmePi_cgqnH61O6h4kmoNmLKsmOUI54z-aXteQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I don’t know man. To pay 3.50 cents for a coffee, ordering the same coffee at other locations perfectly the same order but then come here and notice that not only was worker passive aggressive. But did not apologize or speak the fact that they did not make the coffee properly.

It’s 2024. Why can’t we make our own coffee..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Oh my word..  I thought I'd go on a whim and try a cold beverage for the first time and so stoked I did. This is now my favorite coffee!! Got a 'Cold Brew with Cinammon Almond Foam' and customized with a splash of soy milk and cinnamon powder topping. Absolutely delicious!
One of my reasons to not hesitate this time was that I saw Starbucks have now ditched the straws and have fully recyclable take out cups! Finally, I'm so glad they're doing their part and changed my decision on cold beverages.
Convenient mobile ordering in advance and pickup from the joint is super easy, convenient and allows a lot of granularity when customizing your order as well as COVID friendly/collect some loyalty points for your troubles. Make sure you check the offers in the app before ordering as you need to activate the offer before committing!
The staff are awesome, skilled baristas and extremely friendly. A fantastic location outside the skytrain station, comfortable, clean and well maintained coffee house with nice restrooms. Unfortunately no indoor seating due to COVID, but there is plenty of outdoor seating available!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5dDJKMQOXW5T9nE2aMjqSlrx-Ffh1-wlm04eh&fid=0x0:0x4348892232f8aef8"],"When":"2021-2-4"},{"Name":"Gurpreet Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJrR9f7DMrg_iWaySW1y8d_Co_us7ZcQ5OVV8UvdG_iH15zGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst location of Starbucks I’ve ever been to I waited 20 minutes just for my coffee. The Asian girl working there is way too slow and was taking 15 minutes just to make one coffee. If you know there’s rush hour why only 2 employees were working there? Awful service would never go to this location again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sam Chambell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL5Fq3vWFITYJrrv3a3z6b5jnD94_tq_zMv1IQyt0ffTGvzvw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I love their music, but it's wayyy to loud on the east side of the coffee shop. It's blasting everytime I come in, to a point where I actually just leave and don't stay for very long. I absolutely love their choices in music but it's so hard to study/focus when music is blasting so loud. In addition, there's a total black out zone in almost the entire Starbucks; calls don't even go through, and wifi/data don't work. It's been like this for like 3-4 years - don't know how or why they haven't fixed this. It's not just my devices; when I've come here w friends - they've shared the same issue.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"PLAYA PLAYA Studios","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6CE1c2sT_o6375D08yi2FTr2T6vkzV4U73QserhJXZnFn7u6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sensed a bit of hostility from the workers, seemed too concerned with my presence in the store. Food and drinks were great though!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sumaiya Hossain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfgMXtqbMn3ZJZSZnczXmBg7n73cK3UZZUFJkpjeYu-k9SrUg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to get some coffee for me and my family. I had a fantastic time at Starbucks, and Naimul, the assistant manager, provided exceptional service. He's not only kind but also incredibly efficient in his work. Will definitely revisit the store .","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"SJ Kwak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWLECfVhFzw3UImajK4duWa1rotww1Cfjc1bWi3JPYgw23toMh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I go to Metrotown often to eat, but this is the healthiest and most enjoyable meal I've had.
TIKI, YUZU, and KOKO are all delicious, The ingredients, including the vegetables, are very fresh and the ratio to rice is just right.
I think I'll come here often~👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsqvsiN1Z9n8V2WXBZMTRHFA5LQvmH7zJSouho&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Jemma Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXCHgsvEOda8Euj2F1UAraubpKMT6WV7yVIZRrlelmuyGL9zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bowl was full of flavour, variety of veggies and toppings and protein! I love that they don’t overprice their chicken, because I don’t eat fish, thank you! Looking forward to trying the other bowls with chicken and different sauces. The staff was very friendly. I really enjoyed this poke lunch, much better than the other poke places I’ve tried! (Some of them don’t even have chicken)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3m_XOgt7umAMi8Kg3ZR97-0JYgURpKRDswMjW&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Hye Young Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYtZQewHWsS6Wii6BMW5k2iV0tNbv0D_WAgNrxSvdbZp6ZeZq-Rg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Hula Poke Bowl in Metrotown and had a fantastic experience. The restaurant was clean and had a bright, welcoming atmosphere that made me feel right at home.The menu offered a great variety of options, catering to all dietary preferences with vegan and gluten-free choices. I ordered the classic poke bowl of the Koko with salmon, Kimch, and it was incredibly fresh and flavorful. The ingredients were vibrant and well-balanced, and the portion size was generous for the price.Service was top-notch; the staff was friendly and quick to help me customize my bowl exactly how I wanted it. I also appreciated the speedy service, as my meal was prepared in just a few minutes. For those visiting for the first time, I highly recommend trying the spicy Gochujang sauce—it added a perfect kick to the bowl. Overall, Hula Poke Bowl is a great spot for a healthy and delicious meal in Metrotown. I'll definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqkWf0hvAWSXxGvGes4ctX1Ipdhmf6vm7_FE9B&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItsH-SV0bfKKKu6qfT1W87B-UsOjX8GXGip3whqQWEPEJBqQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Poke is high quality with fresh ingredients, big portion and reasonable price. Hula poke Metrotown is the best in Vancouver","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsMhkPn8JQ1bAh_1GlGFEzPmuPfwQyZROPq_aO&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Michelle Siaril","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvNHVR_L-5eCK2usU0kQoT055SV9vB2qDNPyrA7CmG9QXO2IM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried Hula after a shopping trip in Metrotown.  It’s more of a 3.5 stars for me. Tbh all the ingredients were fresh, and I enjoyed the different variety of bowls they have. That said, I really don’t think this qualifies as poke, it’s more like a salad with lots of poke toppings. With that said, I got the Tropical and really enjoyed the pineapple and toasted coconut flake toppings. Service was lovely and the ladies were super helpful and prompt.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpkcypnr1bin8othA6pAzttAcjYm2A4j7ZoYQ&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Yerim H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuhy3x2hMyII3cc8tq6eIIvlnRm388HHZ7ndz-menwfVVCqJLA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hula Poke is my go-to place for lunch. I appreciate their healthy ingredients and I'm sure it's definitely the best meal in the food court. Most restaurants just buy commercially available sauces, but this Hula Poke uses healthy, gluten-free ingredients and makes all the sauces directly in the kitchen, giving it a very unique and fantastic taste. I usually order Yuzu or Tiki with salmon as my protein and coconut rice as the base, and it's always so delicious. I also love their wild Ahi Tuna, so sometimes I choose both salmon and tuna for double the protein, or half salmon and half tuna without additional cost. The staff here always adds more protein than other branches, so I'm really grateful. Besides, other poke brands require additional costs for additional ingredients, but it's really nice that Hula Poke add ingredients at no additional cost except for Protein. I love that I can add my favorite expensive avocado for free. Friendly staff always provides kindness and best service, and their price is much affordable, which is $15.5 for all included. I really appreciate that Hula Poke is located in Metrotown Mall. Thanks a lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZIg1W3ut52N52RQIThZx2hpqbHUjhjSYfadZx&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Passion c","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKy9fOFfR9Fag40R8ofxdF5xkLC7WGpfnNlcNGr_VGtHeRIB2N_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience at this restaurant! I ordered the TIKI bowl with salmon and coconut rice, and it was delicious. The amount was just right for one person. I also tried the LAVA (like iced café latte) and YUZU tea, and they were both fantastic. The staff mentioned that there is no sugar in them, which was a nice surprise. The shop is right next to the food court, not inside it. The staff were kind and the food was delicious. I highly recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2kjg3A1RpTLfkhSRtBUKKiF82wEwEJQeB8mh0&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-2-9"},{"Name":"Gloria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD74LOIa8MWcISA9W4hyymCIUX6a5UMPTQTVWm5feeT6iBNTk4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All "poke" bowls are made with careful consideration for health and unique luxury taste. Every time I eat "Hula Poke", I feel healthy, and my stomach feels comfortable. I can say it's definitely the best healthy option in the Foodcourt of Metrotown. I especially recommend their Tiki, Yuzu, and Koko (spicy Korea). "Tiki" is a truly special and amazing taste that I've experienced for the first time. "Yuzu" tastes like soy sauce based and is a bit salty, but you can ask for less sauce if you don't like salty taste. All "poke bowls" are always fresh and of good quality, unlike the cheap ingredients. The Metrotown branch (located near the entrance to the food court) is very friendly and clean and provides generous amounts of protein. So I always come here on purpose, and if I can't come, I order a poke bowl through "DoorDash". I am always very satisfied and recommend you to visit too.

Oh, I almost forgot to recommend their delicious "lava" coffee, so I'm adding it now. The latte is made with 100% plant-based coconut milk and is dairy-free, making it super healthy. I want to drink this lava coffee every day. The taste is so great and they make it one by one when you order. Definitely the best, you should try it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMb2Z7hwy9MUae1Xs9KXJfkiUGSb2b9UTDSA7ax&fid=0x0:0x7e7c7e258692f75b"],"When":"2024-2-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ayon Rayhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUk1t0mMEnXcBwA4oO2vbDly8NCDTs72Gk7ZzS-nvuFcnUdEkL8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is nice little cafe where the owner Mr. Yasser welcomes you with a warm smile. He solely does everything and from scratch. The menu is limited consisting of sandwich salads soup and drink. The service is homely so is the food. The best thing is it's very cheap and the quality is top notch. I tried the roast beef sandwich and the turkey sandwich and added soup in the side. The quantity along with the quality was really good. I really enjoyed it and would totally recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMI4TEvgtDwZkGIH8x2Vh2AyOlviZxJ1cI_JBo&fid=0x0:0x4f540f85a76e3a80"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"Samra Shah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIswPeFCVvLsO9ejGTyiRV0cerwlzJ6_2Wy1oMFekFq3_UE00M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden gem. Love uncle yaser and his smiling face and personality. His lentil and chicken noodle soups are the best. Tried His rice with salmon and that was top notch. Don't forget to try their corn beef and chicken sandwiches. Everything was just amazing. Did I mention it was reasonable too!! Highly recommended halal spot in town.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elan Hollander","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnIlVLclphuHwqKMxUF9McwyEgadvGeftskP8rgiFSS8Jcxeaj_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My gf and I were looking for a soup and sandwich and chose Yassers Cafe because we saw the great google reviews and we were not disappointed! A cozy, cheap eats diner, Yasser was welcoming and friendly from the moment we walked in. The sandwiches were $6 and they were just what we were looking for. Yasser is a gracious and wonderful owner who gave us free chocolates and made us feel like a part of his community. Definitely recommend if you’re in the Burnaby area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNifgAZba-fZta0cfCreZ_VHtSdQXG4NuHR2ceJ&fid=0x0:0x4f540f85a76e3a80"],"When":"2022-12-6"},{"Name":"starfinder1234","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuJA6PrxL3Yh7DTk7a8nlD0e2diwxYtLvXKrhUJ5UoxzS4Iw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time visit today. Hard working owner and so down to earth. Food is great and unbelievably cheap considering the high quality. I wish this type of business all the success in the world","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Avril Metcalfe-Roach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYGU1Ys5Qyc5eCX8FcN5yk2cuQlc_xMGZCyUKu8z6nL3BA4-Lo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, what an amazing gem! Very affordable, excellent atmosphere, and delicious food. I got a soup, sandwich, and latte for $9, and it's all homemade in the best way. I plan on coming here a lot.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tristan Dellazizzo Toth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVZJymYfvZrIq0AjRoxrr2A4It6JQn8Vs4-DrN8tPvYDYOKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got a coffee and some lunch there.  Tasty home-cooked food and an excellent coffee.  Very friendly owner who takes pride in charging very affordable prices.  Tax included in all the postings too.  Definitely would recommend to anyone in the area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Noorain Fareed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ4rcqgzd6GmpbSObgU-qk1NtARKFswmS5LUkqIRn2ehzmFgA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yasser’s Café is more than just a place to grab a bite—it's an experience crafted with heart and soul. This cozy little spot offers a level of warmth and personal attention that’s hard to find anywhere else.
Each dish is prepared fresh and with care, reflecting Yasser’s passion for good food.

With no other staff, Yasser handles everything himself, and yet, he never makes you feel like he’s too busy. He welcomes you as if you’re an old friend, taking time to chat, share a laugh, and make sure you’re enjoying your meal. It’s this personal touch that turns a simple visit into a memorable experience. You feel less like a customer and more like a guest in Yasser’s home.

If you’re in the area and looking for a spot that offers great taste with even better hospitality, Yasser’s Café is the place to go. It may be small and simple, but the warmth and care you’ll receive here are truly unmatched.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhGjy80CTfRvhVu68W48jKztX73xZkk29Zgnse6nPEawcoaawB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing dining experience and vibes. Service was excellent and the food was such good value. Make sure you get the soup + sandwich combo

Will be sure to come back again! Great neighborhood gem and so charming","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipME8Vfr03eW4kjyoH7iFkfKSsfvVreHrrTFCiI&fid=0x0:0x4f540f85a76e3a80"],"When":"2022-2-2"}]
