[{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Little hidden gem in this medical building.  Good amount of parking spots behind the building and underground.

Great tiramisu souffle pancake - very soft and fluffy. You have to wait for 20min because they just make to order.   It's $20 each but it's big enough for 4 people!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPv4Fa4Xl01ozfMEKtNFzq4C-B0tjp0GJ9yz5Hp&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Camilia Rodriguez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWigkoqaNhHJinW1sDEWmiP5-QkCbLl16QFp5xZiy1DDMYI0dmUuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for some studying time and it has been great. I got a tiramisu to start which was so tasty! I just couldn’t finish it by myself. I also ordered a spicy tuna poke bowl and it was delicious. The service is great, they page you for your food and drinks, they also provide these nice wooden trays with which you can take your items to the table. The seating varies depending which table you sit at. It looks like their soufflé pancakes are where it’s at so i’ll have to come back and try them soon. Great food and tranquil study spot. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ five starts from me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcj03xALUBYH-hOxvs4lVdShmAkDc2k2Kg9BDg&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The highlight here is their jiggly, airy, puffy, soufflé pancakes 🥞. Tried the brown cheese one and the brown cheese was delicious. The only thing is their whipped cream is too sweet and overpowers everything with the taste of sugar as the soufflé already comes drizzled in syrup too. Wish they had an option for unsweetened whipped cream. The matcha latte was great quality with tons of matcha in it and tasted very good. Spinach scrambled eggs with toast was also solid. Great place for brunch and coffee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKNPsMgoEm0zaOM5gHFckO9OajU-UpIkknCicd&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Seulwon Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-NBijG6OLnoPAXkqZZsyMx973iNOZiaSOgvjp-XTuuw-Uug=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited this café today, and the atmosphere was absolutely wonderful!

The vanilla latte was smooth and perfectly sweet, making it so easy to enjoy.

The Einspänner was so cute and delicious with its creamy top. This café truly made my day feel even more perfect.

The staff were friendly, and the cozy interior made me want to stay longer. I’ll definitely visit again! Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQZMaR7P3Tcdcmwl5JjabjQTWogUhIJ_SrEa4x&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-12-26"},{"Name":"Macho Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWToXpU3H3YB3xkMOp6uUKU5gePr0KH9w6w89u7rGCD3siyx0IX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Both the pancake and the coffee are nice.
The brown cheese favour is special and tastes very nice, the dish even comes with an icecream.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYicG37ArDNrJ4_vQdm729p5gsaGvuOtnZc33k&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hiel Cafe’s food taste pretty good, and its portions are quite good, particularly for the salmon poke. The prosciutto panini’s tomatoes are quite thin though, probably smaller than the thickness of cardboard, BUT tastes super good.

That sandwich with smoked salmon and shrimp CHANGED ME. One of the best I’ve ever tasted.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPn_n_LNxR-yogsCHytr9D4Rt27kZDf5Edsk860&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"Monika Vretenickova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXW0wlOSsfKymo-nWbUPI0tmG0BlkhRpJn7wVHjKqLh9HR5WSUD=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best breakfast place within a few kilometers of my home. If you’ve never tried soufflé pancakes, you absolutely should. While there’s a bit of a wait for them to be prepared, it’s worth every minute. The only downside is that they’re closed on Sundays. I’ve tried every item on their menu, and each one is a piece of heaven.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnzIUPi7gtfAKL6OQSBsYIoPDazuL2TZQMO-9P&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Joey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJl9szXFCvkqiDIj8ffgxhpU02VBcZUaH8smB2SMyI4TIXdsaA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hiel Cafe is a gem! The cafe was creamy and rich, topped with perfectly dusted cocoa powder. The matcha souffle pancake was fluffy, light, and beautifully presented with fresh strawberries. The atmosphere is cozy, perfect for enjoying a quiet morning or working on a laptop. Highly recommend for anyone in search of a delightful cafe experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv_3OHUm4LxD5ueMxpaNyFm5_oLwvWCXg8XX8b&fid=0x0:0x73fb2a980eff29b6"],"When":"2024-6-25"}]

We are so grateful we chose this location. We look forward to returning soon. Great vegan options also. High recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATYlDUT33YaT-jyUWUihUJSVj0xkuYRs8eAT3&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"skr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIcuhU2CLfpC2Z6zhqf2JvPfEX3PFzkuNqk6OK8TD1kgxyFdg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m kinda disappointed that I didn’t come here to celebrate my birthday earlier. The services and the vibes are amazing!!! The servers are welcoming and friendly. I was given free cakes for my birthday as well. However, I still paid them based on the price of the cakes. There is a happy hour after 9pm. The price is reasonable considering the enchanting romantic atmosphere. The light of the candles provided a beauty effect on my face when taking photos. You definitely wouldn’t mind tipping a little bit more. I will come back here very soon!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsrMrn3QKFi_i-0pivElQLLscc640Zz8pxkIcy&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Hassan Makhlouf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYREoqUkazVJoJhrGCrjS5g1lIMahzFkhsZA1Ir7O3A-YofJyb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went celebrating family member birthday. I like their food a lot but these small things makes a difference.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOef9pM2BQzUyFk2_F-L-NPBAaBZkn-Smu8Ma_0&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Ashkan N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGC9QpVpAYzkuU2nETbRxXDGZW6ZxU4DFK0Bytd5fdamCstw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited this location for the first time a couple of weeks ago for drinks and some appetizers. Been always eating at the restaurant and the size is doubled. Cactus has ruined its reputation. Well, don’t ever order their food if you can’t dine in, they treat you like dumb trash. If a restaurant only earns money from tips, why don’t just shut down the takeout service?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMD8jkA6r1Y0e7CnucdwCw608P487717s_XxZki&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Sara Rostami","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-0F0X5uejpgUPksS3dNe8lvbqXi3gXIV5sSqvv6JCvVyYEIfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my favorite Cactus Club Cafe location of all. I managed to book a nice table on the patio for my friend’s birthday. Despite the restaurant being nearly full, the service was excellent, and the food was delicious. We spent a wonderful three hours there and will definitely be back again, as always.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObjOW_YZD9aV_zLjIUsOibPIc0NnCIuqWU7H7n&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Stanley Lowe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMA0j5YPV0e_ki7txxd7xeDBLDLGeQTP8WAcMSalz9cV9eFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Sunday night Happy Hour.

Got the steak and frites.  It came with a kale salad, too.  It was $26.50.

The avocado 🥑  and chips was shared among the table.  It was quite good.

Service was consistent.

It was quite busy for a Sunday night.

Good music and lots of parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPup812y4Z5GBQ-agBQ_b_P59lzdx6HDFr7SHRO&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Joshua Lamb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpxxroB9wWkDP81-bzqi9m3qKH73kXPdF1qlay8Miqx3mQiFLjRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A friend brought me here and the moment I walked in I felt like it was a high end restaurant. Though it has that vibe, the prices are fair and absolutely perfect for the great quality of food they create.

The sirloin steak, with mash and salad, was next to perfect. We got the steak and it was slighlytly over cooked and asked of it could be rare, which they quite nicely remade it and took care of us. The service was absolutely brilliant and rarely see such amazing waiters as this.

The atmosphere is great and the happy hour was fun to get drinks like margaritas and spritz. Highly recommended!

Overall, I enjoyed the experience even though I was worried about food, service and atmosphere. They went above and beyond and for that, I give this place 5 stars all around. Way to go Cactus Club Cafe!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoULAVkEGVY3jTkCN_SiUcS2TxS_8V2n4b6Bbs&fid=0x0:0x47d677bf5b06211e"],"When":"2024-6-30"}]

I’m have been using the app for the longest time & I always get great service from All the other Starbucks:  avoid Brentwood mall location","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nina Nina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZbhZJX3HEueZZLpxqPXabLicizPKFLrhaJLmmuYYZ0h2qxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They refused service several times and did not sell me a donut and coffee.They  excused themselves that they don't have a change from 100 cad bill. I brought a 100 dollar bill, I went with this 100 bill to another place (not Sturbucks), and I've got excellent service there. The worst service in the world that I received at this Brentwood Starbucks location. I'll never go there again till the rest of my life.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cinematic Street","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCp2f1A-In1bpp3loogksA-Xwpv81Z3SBe1YH0vraCE77A3vdn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This area of Burnaby is called the Brentwood District and this Starbucks Coffe Shop is part of a mall called the Amazing Brentwood.  The name is appropriate because the architecture is stunning in every direction.  The Starbucks itself is no exception, because it has a fabulous design and is perched majestically on the edge of a plaza that overlooks the Brentwood Town Centre Skytrain and the Lougheed Highway.  The views at this Starbucks are amazing, inside and out.  It’s a photographers dream coffee shop.

The mall was formerly called the Brentwood Towne Centre.  The entire neighbourhood is a huge development in Burnaby.  It’s a very popular place to live and work.  There are tons of stores nearby so you can shop till you drop.  Then come to Starbucks for some R&R.  The location is perfect for access or a meetup, because it’s literally right beside the Skytrain.  You can’t miss it.  It usually has a water fountain out front which adds to the experience, but sadly it wasn’t working on the day I visited.

This Starbucks sits on top of a McDonalds, and both places have large windows to sit beside and watch the world go by.  Starbucks has a unique wrap around corridor with ample seating so that you can get a good view, no matter where you sit.  Lots of light to say the least.  Perfect for the long Vancouver winters where light is the most valuable commodity.  Even the McDonalds below the Starbucks appears to have a very interesting open concept design.

I was working on a tower nearby so I had to be at work early, and thankfully the Starbucks was open.  Their hours are amazing.  5:30AM-10:30PM on most days.  Great for construction workers or anyone with unusual  work hours.  Shooting the Starbucks at night was almost more interesting than the daytime because the light is so dramatic.  I also came to Starbucks during the day for coffee, and also took more pictures.  My day ended at 8:30PM so I was able to snap a few more night pictures at Starbucks, grab some of their delicious Avocado spread which I'm kind of addicted too, before hopping on the train.

As usual, wifi, food, ambiance, and coffee was great.  I know what I’m getting at Starbucks and I love that predictability.  Also, the staff were excellent.  Very friendly and helpful.  I was so surprised to see the option to tip the staff with a card.  Usually most Starbucks require a manual cash tip.  The nice barista said that this new tipping method “may” be rolled out to all Starbucks.  That would be great, as cash isn’t the most convenient thing to carry around.

All around great coffee shop in a very attractive mall that sits in a very attractive part of Burnaby.  Brentwood is popular and appears to be thriving.  Lots of towers going up around here, for good reason.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXrPk4nn0x2hbUaNye5kS4vjhFfnblTAolt3uZ&fid=0x0:0xd0051032d291910b"],"When":"2023-4-6"},{"Name":"Edgar Ignacio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7oexz4qXoBKr6ujKuYxwMvlf16ckv-ovFMKFmC4nzUqeMSoelFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good location along Brentwood district with ample amount of seating inside the shop. They offer outside seats with their outdoor patio overlooking the beautiful view outside like the water fountain and others. Service was great but they needed more staff to accommodate the sudden influx of people making the que with longer wait time. My total amount of time spent from ordering to getting my order is about 34 minutes on my estimate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEb8dXnA8t5jszbnfm3wcCRmmAJQdkefENmDX-&fid=0x0:0xd0051032d291910b"],"When":"2023-8-16"}]

[{"Name":"San Wayne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjFb2dB41O9n_VFwgfqlyajgDnGhNggu7YKnObZ04VikDc3OZS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my 3rd time to have meal on this restaurant. Waiter is good and environment is silent and clean. But the food quality is worst. The green bean is hard to chew with the root. It seems not Japanese made food quality. And the rice is coming very soft and not taste as before good. The food inside steamed egg is very few. It is only fish cake, spinach on top of the steamed egg which is not as Japanese style. Hope to be improved in the future","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXlV8AHHPc7K_NaO3S05LvcSz_aC2ncCUR4v2z&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"Kepler F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcYUwrLRUf_A4xgkkfabw9Aa43ECXLeHl3hlCTWCXfL2zpbI0l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"🌟 A Tempura Paradise at Tendon Kohaku! 🍤

If you're a fan of crispy, golden tempura with flavors that transport you straight to Japan, Tendon Kohaku in Metrotown is a must-visit. The moment I stepped in, the warm aroma of freshly fried tempura set the stage for an unforgettable meal.

Their signature bowls are a masterpiece of texture and flavor. The perfectly crispy tempura paired with their unique sauces strikes a balance that’s both comforting and exciting. I particularly loved the prawn and vegetable mix—each bite felt like a celebration of fresh ingredients and expert craftsmanship.

The ambiance is cozy yet modern, and the staff are incredibly friendly and attentive, making the dining experience even better. Despite the lunch rush, my food arrived quickly and piping hot—a testament to their efficiency and care.

Pro tip: Go hungry! The portions are generous, and you’ll want to savor every bite. Don’t forget to pair your meal with their refreshing side options for the complete experience.

Tendon Kohaku is easily one of Metrotown’s culinary gems. Whether you're a tempura enthusiast or new to this Japanese delight, this spot is bound to impress. I’ll definitely be back! 🍚✨","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMORejluv2j8f4kmRNF3iFOrteuDvoCB3ROxuHw&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"cotton candy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMmoOGXJIlT8jx0uCPFlNxGb2g2JZ9w1U-ngpkfzafqh4mlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It gave me a menu, but it was really convenient to order food quickly on the monitor. There was no time to wait for the server, so it was convenient. The food tasted good, but Tendon was especially delicious. It's a restaurant I visit more than once a year.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1qwMoqAAY6f001UQf6yNpX97J_ryNm7QoUXUL&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Mrs. Leci","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFUu7tIDGHhiFP61EOIZLCOSzvwJkGN10CXxqa6MRhYpyxpm4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I've tried their food a few times already and I was hoping the food and service would step up. I must say that if not because of the sauce, it won't be as tasty. Their price is on average and also, there's not so many dish options to choose from, which is fine because they focus on their signature dishes.

Hope that our next visit will be better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrA-f95TMAg4kbL2U1JlRB04AlaSNbnuHLtqWr&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love this place. The ambiance reminds me of Japan. Food was good too. The server was a Japanese lady. Her service was pleasant, typical of a Japanese restaurant.

Had the rice bowls, chicken, and chawan mushi. Will definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTUnBh7Wmpn3XdSSK4QFwhiEWRnfbpoI6bLB4b&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"gold stream","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMLKdGRVpixSTb9Y3fj1pK-hK-7pRtDNbg9D1Y6Usg47nrsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This Tendon Kotaku is located between Metrotown mall and Crystal mall in Burnaby. Opens at 11:30am serving Japanese tempura  style seafood and pork cutlet on rice or udon noodles. Their curry dishes are aromatic and not too spicy. Most items are under twenty dollars, the place is clean and tidy. Service is reasonable with only two servers and one robot. You can order through the touchscreen display on the table which is very easy for the small menu. Food quality and quantity is good and consistent. Don't forget to add the savory egg custard on your order. Washrooms are clean. One of the better restaurants in the area. Recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQ_XzOrf8_13TPlpFQELSOob000KYvigYI1VSz&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Amnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjcm2KnVvAXZsXO1Xw9a-BsRGj5-RmJ6nF12OqCF9XTomoPJ9CkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is located conveniently and has a beautiful interior. Lots of seating is available.

The service is pretty decent, and you've got a little tablet to make your orders, with everything divided into different categories. Some of the pictures are very misleading though, like the fact that tendons don't come with the side dishes.

Regardless, the food itself was great, and so was the tea. The portions were good, so you get good value.

Overall, just be mindful of what you're actually getting when you order.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNby3wY2pC3FwMEjugvK9y_hDzJ3m0Xdnugzo03&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Love the bottomless salad, rice, and miso soup add on option for $2.99. The aesthetic is pretty, artful, and super clean and nice. They seem understaffed but the service when you did get it was great and kind. You can ring a bell on the iPad to get your server to come to your table and you order from an iPad on each table and you can even request refills from your iPad.

The only downside is I found the taste of the tempura to be quite mediocre. The crust was not the crispiest and it was quite oily. The flavours of everything were quite average and nothing stood out. The rice was on the harder and drier side as well. The best food items were the cabbage salad and the miso soup which were delicious. The anago tendon and the sashimi aimori tendon were both average tasting, but the deep fried runny egg was great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeIUu5sr2c-yQgQS57WNaiy9FZl3jCqV0U2Hhb&fid=0x0:0x42b9fc24a08d3e4e"],"When":"2024-8-2"}]

The carrot cake was our favourite; moist and packed with carrot flavour. The cookies are large and quite flat in size, but still delectable. The croissant was average. Parking is very limited in the area, and appears to be primarily in a pay parking lot. The items were decent, and would like to try their other offerings in the future!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbuuuHLs-oIMIn1_UjY0P_WEz4sx9Bkn8Rej0F\u0026fid=0x0:0x6bf16b0adb2db607"],"When":"2022-11-9"},{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQmqmJDqNbwLx2VMpVLCBMInhyiTULu5QDr35uuDm9RLFH0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The person working there was friendly and quick. It was not toasted properly, I was very disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our workplace had ordered some gluten friendly/vegan treats which were tasty. There are 5 locations throughout Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRa0GcqFiphWuuojd3qUOomn9EgvjAtz7-BTAE\u0026fid=0x0:0x6bf16b0adb2db607"],"When":"2022-11-27"},{"Name":"Mohammad M Islam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuRqeYa0qeQvQy57V-9LRvbVMV5FXbbaQqt8771B7XbII3uUko6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice little eatery hidden in the office blocks between Gilmore and Canada Way. [{"Name":"Maria M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmuhUB-INQ3XCbE2M9HT-MdzILSuqxW6ls6tLvy0JgUoxl1f3wCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A gem! Truly hidden and open very few times a week. It’s more of a grab and go, since there’s no tables. Great options and service (explaining the drinks…), made from coffee lovers to coffee lovers. Very cute merchandise available, adorable decoration and details. The Vienna was so delicious! The espresso con panna also perfection!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR9fsYzQBdVCegw5H_UHMAOMJ_H3VSYfgiG20K&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2023-6-28"},{"Name":"Sacha Bourdeau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRUh8-imnd3wzM4JOv8PNroQ7FD5h_F6kSDycXfW7bMaPV7g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very quaint small location (still found a seat for an hour and there is a couch for a group) that is bursting with character. Soft older music plays, the staff greets you warmly and provide hospitable service during your whole visit. The matcha here is unavailable to buy in North America, it is straight from Japan and it is everything i dreamed matcha could be, no sugar needed with no bitterness, just pure delicate flowery softness. I can't wait to bring my wife here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harrison Ens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXy6nnUCtAVE291ykxHAR5AkhEKCNqUnONOVioWeL9fWaUVxpaY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The flavour of the espresso dances on your tongue. The employee measures each ingredient on a digital scale. This is the best Flat White I have found in Burnaby thus far.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRsL77zMc_jZBaE71jUNTzsrHfz64EpvunX_YG&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Stacey Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLsWi_XXrkXimr1ZHvMUqc6PGN2xnjFgOPSJXuoWLODzVmewj1l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely little coffee shop. They choose their own beans, which you can buy as well. Lots of small Japanese goods for purchase as well as organic loose leaf tea. The hojicha latte was delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNydSqAZPzWoag90NV1E8Mpddd8ScVG1eJuJxN&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2019-6-30"},{"Name":"Catherine Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTkz5822W-4tHOlQW0f2BS3SRckLjhOraB3PjIPXcn_UMUsmbO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cafe is such a hidden gem! I tried the hojicha latte and was blown away. Even after I had taken my photos of the latte art, capped the latte, and taken it outside, I could smell the decadent wafts of hojicha scent from the drink. It smelled soooo good and tasted so good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMhsqb6LnXOnz-udffWLfkU_XwnclgUrHYRC8e&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Rose Kiahna Dee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Xd6qzkztFC2NElF6RT1ndjILxyYRdBA9nYWxRhqkTa78ajel=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love everything about this place. So the owner roasts the coffee in house and weighs and measures everything to perfection. I love capuccinos and the last few sips were my favourite. Very friendly and a hidden gem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_XTJFXDqqE4jhhIroBszr_FoAAnLCd9DrcB1B&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Vic Yung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjSUFpvFSwHsCrywPzGZzN7WDhV8Ljlj3YECw07iwjqMR_leW5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went on a Saturday afternoon. The store is tiny, so may be hard to spot just driving by. There is free street parking available in the residential area adjacent, but may be hard to find depending on the time of day.

The storefront is quite charming and has a rustic, home-y feel to it.

Ordered a matcha latte and Japanese latte, both of which were made upon ordering. Both came with latte art, which was a nice touch. The matcha latte has the option of adding sweetener (and how much), which allows for customization. The matcha latte was not overly sweet with 1 pump added, and allowed for the match flavour to come through.

Since the space is so small, there is not really any room to stay and drink. Would recommend for a quick visit, perhaps in the warmer months so that you can take a walk afterwards.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2qlMKBikCLdwrNYQkdE6-0E_EDzeIuE4_yeK5&fid=0x0:0xf6fac893c25bc62a"],"When":"2023-3-14"},{"Name":"Jeong In Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhT-3rLqCUHs0eGs-Cft-r-2PqXROGBbR4quhAB71v-u93HK_t=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The male owner was incredibly rude. I was looking forward to trying some new coffee, especially since it was a Japanese café. When I asked him for a recommendation, he just said, “Well, nothing.” I then asked what their signature drink was, and he replied, “It depends on what you like.” Honestly, he could have easily mentioned their best-seller or responded more politely.

The coffee itself was nothing special. I’d rather go to JJ Bean—they have better coffee and much better customer service.","Images":null,"When":""}]

(It has its own parking spot within the building, and you can find the entrance on the Wilson Ave side.) The only thing I didn’t like was that the server, although nice, kept checking our table more than necessary, which became a bit disruptive. Even though the restaurant wasn’t very busy, I didn’t understand why the server kept coming to our table to ask if we were done or seemed surprised that we were still eating, especially when there were plenty of empty tables. other than that, everything was good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgcKsFZMZrtxtUAOKfP7Er5jE6CJ6Uz__veRxX&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Kkkim B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLOfRrWEMi_vvY3iDdyONtrSsnnVdNP1hCnl_hUc3gu4dvsw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love it. Went there for the 1st time on a friend's recommendation. I think their price, food and quality are better than the one I usually go in New Westminster. A chicken skewer was marinated well and not dry at all. Moussaka was really good as well. I even ordered another dish for take out for my family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjWu8rOgOD-69E8Ar73t7A7hOYB9hfgr4RPsxn&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is good, great service and quick. lots of deliveries going out while I was there.. people coming and enjoying themselves.. portions at good size.. price is on point.. can’t complain much about the place..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMU0QVH6_oSGWbHrymxi0vhH3csIDcXna_5SG2r&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Mohit Owan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLdXlXw47UFGmP-UZGr5PN2Ez8idbUYa3WUwQErzVQ8T7Jkxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and great atmosphere! Some of the best Greek food you can have in town. Can’t go wrong with the chicken and prawn souvlaki","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3kxMsUV9Nxq4Zxl1G_GAHwhuWRqIDSofL-lvc&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"AIZY A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW63HuUeCCv9sgK_rgm18cZfVwLP0r1WfmUCdIu1jqRWz_XpAFKzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was okay, very friendly server. We didn't wait that long for the food its just that its not that hot when we got our plate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLgjx0ZxzSj_lI6gFRt4pA-qExMDeABCiiuARx&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Sylvia Wunder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLWnKi7DdZM7EeOp25GCd1l8J1-L_rYXXZI7qi-_AM1rn-2I7t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is great … always. I love the saganaki and chicken souvlaki dinner. Without fail, consistent. They will even make the saganaki gluten free on request.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSihVa2v13sin85wxiYHxUZPgyJYsLAHX3PoFW&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"The Koki Channel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYCAfLKhUq--7x95Yhvc2vGemFeI_RXxT_ZXun36dUV2kGKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lamb dishes are very tasty. Authentic Greek food available. Chef was very helpful to make aware of allergy ingredients. Pleasant service staff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0yIwS_uvz-Aua0-V1w3nHjx0CE55_uc69gC-l&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Sarah W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXT0nZvuCCWtxE7tCmKwkdtK9DgTxxgPN_H5tcLUmMEgLxeACiU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our all time favourite restaurant in the neighborhood of Metrotown/Crystal Mall Burnaby.

The portions are large, the service is friendly and easy parking at the back.  Lots of takeout and pickups while we are there so you know the food is great!

We went there before 6pm on Saturday evening for two of us. The place was already 80%full. If you have a group of 5 or more, highly recommend to reserve your table ahead of time.

We ordered and share the Calamari appetizer, I always ordered the Moussaka and hubby had the Roast Lamb.

We have tried the Garlic Shrimp appetizer also and it was hot and full of dipping garlic butter.

The Pita bread is crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside.

Our meals come with Greek Salad, Potato, Veggie and Rice. We had to pack our meal home and it was great the next day also. There were enough Roast Lamb also for hubby's lunch on Monday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO30lB8uvBmr7Eg8eFHxDKwXKzhw3az_SNvGtIv&fid=0x0:0xd426c329a9fec480"],"When":"2022-7-4"}]

[{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had hey tea for the first time in china and am so glad they have one here! Drinks taste super similar to the og ones in china so it’s good :) my go to is the mango coconut one and it comes with toppings and it’s sooo delicious. Their 100% sugar is not sweet at all and the drink tastes good even if it’s not mango season. I also tried the grape one a couple times and I think that’s what they’re known for and it’s also super delicious, even if I’m not a big fan of grape flavoured things :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNL9oYymSLFwydHtz60X_MvF4BxuW5eg4cdMt8O&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Hornson C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmdCOdf2WkxshuYZj4HJ9-vQ7jEjZprqyHTmAPfOUXSG3SYvc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"《🧋 REAL MILK, REAL FRUIT, REAL TEA 🧋》

- mango grapefruit sago = $8.99 -
- brown sugar bobo oat milk = $9.99 -

It's been over 12 years since Hey Tea served up their first ever cup of cheese tea in Guangdong Province. Now they've brought their top quality drinks to Crystal Mall in Burnaby for you to enjoy!

They boast using only real ingredients in their tea creations, and you can taste the quality with each sip. Of the two drinks I tried, the mango grapefruit sago was definitely the stand out choice. My fiance noted that every ingredient in that drink was cut up to the perfect size so that nothing would get stuck in the straw. Seems basic, but it's a detail that a lot of other stores fail to pay attention to.

The brown sugar in the second drink was strong but not overpowering. I really liked the taste of the roasted cane sugar and soft, but chewy tapioca pearls. I know Hey Tea is known for their real milk, but I am very appreciative for their non-dairy options for lactose-intolerant people like myself 🥹

Don't wait! Make sure to go and check out Hey Tea the next time you're in Burnaby!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0m4XaPuFmnP28SDNB943maaVwi6_WxirEhbTH&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"Cheryl Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvN7OywIOgBdmkk6UAUdj2t4ZnzVkw9A6vE0EpU3lpnajoA4fzGA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good quality! Taste good and they use good ingredients. Could drink this regularly without feeling bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrK4ftedkyQea-zn3agECmUy1HLo4dTAtSpke8&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Henry Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcTlx45tkivdnVyW4B38kXt4WHZXtLMp6yRttTlIFdf-1gou8R=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not bad, but did not surprise me in any good ways. Now competing with so many tea shops in Vancouver area, I don’t know how long they would survive. Heytea is better in China with many more choices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-Ol0cNLh6g015Emc3zZomuKT2x6LRKg67y6g5&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4NwD3WHKkuCC32KRJYxL65rVHXz6C_MMeVW83zhD6swCLEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The drinks were good but the wait was extremely long on the first grad opening day. It took approximately 30min to line up and order drinks and then another 60min to receive our 4 drinks during their buy 1 get 1 free promotion. The quality of drink was good. Their pick up system was not working as it was stuck on the same screen. I believe they could have improved that to make it more efficiently for people picking up their order.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3zaenygGc83NaGWr9ZVq9XM5ixd_bkWyA6xB0&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2023-10-28"},{"Name":"gabriela reis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOBKemY58IgPosORhIRB3W3KVIoba2dyjWuJDIkQ9qq6LaSTk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The tea was amazing, I think the best experience I had with bubble tea. I am not a big fan of bubble tea, but this took it to a different level.
It took us around 20 min to order and another 50 min to get our drinks. I wouldn’t stop to buy if I see some people waiting already. It was just frustrating.
The place is beautiful, very neat and I love how the drinks looks just like the advertising.
The atmosphere doesn’t fit with the mall, but that’s it. It was just chaos with so many people waiting for the drinks.
Other than this, the drink it is worth a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPA4ibLjrLyotrWTUEiXHpYsw2pDS57geO3Dgbb&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"Zihao Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJts1KPEWXMdTkwsTSfXhyoZW4rvcCXdj436RNqg7a2dRnOsck=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My all time favourite boba tea! Taste is the same as the ones I had in Beijing ☺️ so glad they have a store now in BC! It’s my happy place now","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3UnT_s7JoAFnp6oEpxqouprBro344K3NdVb-g&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Erica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiBiehVBMqDRcQQk3J28lEnqLVQ-p5tIOA0Zlj3wvs65IUmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty decent fruit teas, not your typical bubble tea. Tastes healthier although I'm not sure how true that is.
On the pricy end, but honestly all bubble tea/fruit teas are quite expensive these days so you might as well get some real fruit.

I recommend half sweet for all the drinks, and I got regular ice because they were sort of like slushies.

**Mango Grapefruit Sago ($8.99): I really liked the generous amounts of sago and grapefruit chunks! Nice creamy texture, good mixture of all the toppings (you won't run out of sago before you're done with the drink). This is my second time getting it, probably my fave drink here.

Very Mulberry Heytea ($8.99): This was recommended as a highly popular item, but I'm personally not a fan. It's a dark purple colour, tastes just like grape to me. I don't really like grape generally. Nice slush texture, similar to the mango one.

Pure Regal Aqua Green Jasmine Tea ($4.99): Just a regular ol' jasmine tea. Super light and refreshing for a palate cleanser.

No where to sit! take-out only. You can walk around Crystal Mall or go up to the food court. I came on a Wednesday around 5:30pm, and the wait was about 10min. I saw that they have a QR code if you want to order online.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZmDWOdO7daYY-nGDyociqXW2Ew5HNAedsNhnj&fid=0x0:0xb8907638c7c4754e"],"When":"2024-2-24"}]

[{"Name":"Harrison Ens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXy6nnUCtAVE291ykxHAR5AkhEKCNqUnONOVioWeL9fWaUVxpaY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An excellent location with hard working staff. The Flat White has espresso with a pronounced taste. The Spanish Caffe Latte contained an amazing sweetness & flavour profile.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPULqT7PqJ8lq04vYBiB14qWq2tA2nW5KAOGrWu&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Jisoo Ha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP9G43zEyyMhrfjRW_yt_MDkVCcd0wjhioG4aHmlS1NH_9HRY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love coffee here! One of the best in town.
The location is a bit hidden, but I make the trip just to grab a cup from here. They have a rewards program, which is a plus for a regular. The only thing is that it opens at 11am.. wish it opened earlier!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kit Yee Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy4hyLjXryzPjKJf4N3DUJBAsHtZSSuk76pvxFtVmwfHSV1Gtd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great coffee! Great quality! Great service! Reasonable price.

My husband and I knew this coffee shop for a while but never had a chance to try their coffee. Finally we could taste it today. We ordered their hot latte and iced Creama. It was so good!!! We had a first sip of each one of them. We were addicted to them.

I give 4 stars, because the coffee shop is quite small. Even if there is no covid, it’s hard to sit inside and relax and enjoy a cup of coffee. We have to order takeout and drink the coffee outside.

There are many parking stalls in this complex, so don’t need to worry about parking. This coffee shop is a bit hidden though. It is on the same level of Mr. Paris Bakery and above Hannam Supermarket.

There is another Korean coffee shop right under this one, so there must be competition going on. I hope this coffee shop keeps their good quality and gets more customers to drink their coffee in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMemHcR2zMXevXIx-iUMmbx7Z21aWtqWJbWUsK&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2021-1-31"},{"Name":"Vy Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKM7ZmBV1kG3i8K2Uai2VyeuLdx3nkyWTEoy2ZktnPosYf-Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"*i posted the review on my instagram already and I want to repost it here

I just have came back the 2nd time after having two tasty cups of Choco Mocha & Coffee Latte at my first time. My bf and I was totally impressed.

This time, we got Tiger Eye & Crema. Both taste amazing!! If you enjoy Dalgona coffee, Tiger Eye is the best option for you !! Crema has a creamy milky foam on top and it tastes nicely with the espresso part. GO ENJOY THESE SEASONAL DRINKS (Crema, Tiger Eye, Espresso soda) BEFORE SUMMER REALLY ENDS. ^^

The barista was friendly and nice ^^ There’s only 1 person who’s in charge of the café shop during the day.

I really want this cafe shop to be shouted out widely since its hidden location can be the reason why fewer coffee drinkers come & visit. ☺️

Additionally, there is no seat available inside the store also. You have to sit somewhere outside.

Except for that, their drinks are real must-try 💯

Please kindly support this small local business stronger during this pandemic. They really deserve more loves and supports ☺️

Would highly highly recommend 💯⭐️

#supportlocalbusiness

Photo credit: @thegingerlatte (instagram)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8_tTL_pNCBMuJAqIY9p-jPaCmVwFxETW3rlNM&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2020-10-1"},{"Name":"Vivian Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7lGaNOPkpWTpqjowjqEFuZT3_7uibmWph7_M-U0fFaTpTEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The espresso shot I received this morning had a noticeable bitterness, likely due to being expired. Additionally, it seemed the barista was trying to make several coffees at the same time, which may have contributed to the quality issues.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Loney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhVKtVI_BQxDYH7J6CSEw_I5RbEPGDUzsK9USmRR-WPIXfN9lj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been slade!

First off they have 2 top of the line machines for doing phenomenal pulls of espresso. I forget the first but the second is a Slayer. Simple the best and with a philosophy of keeping new beans coming in all the time they will never leave your palette board.

It's a micro shop with big flavors.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyyrPeHjQ--AIoAF939WThRlhVDCXUEDdFf0aH&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2017-3-19"},{"Name":"Deborah Aiko Insook Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkrXzRxO3A2OGqiLyPY_PlsYk2B44E-xgPkg6UAgy-1KwY7fkT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"May you can miss this place for outside but just follow the way to inside. There are pretty big space to sit for coffee. The barista was kind and bright. I got a long black and good. Try someday when you get Korean essential spot","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPeMBS_VX2V9viwJHnmBm8qfSWArP4k7Q2UEhQ&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2021-7-21"},{"Name":"Stephanie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBV5KRG75WlxmWo1wuDhWSQhlZCOao4V2_9kFkOn0OqRNe45TP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Veroni coffee entrance is very small. It's on the second floor of the Hannam Mart plaza inside the plaza. I had originally come for the Tiger eye coffee but unfortunately they didn't have 3 (out of their Tiger Eye, espressoda and cream) out of the 5 specialty coffees so I had no choice but to try the cloud. The cloud coffee had a strong coffee base. Really liked the flavour of their beans. The cloud on top was a cross between marshmallow and whipping cream. Not too sweet but a bit heavy. The first half of drinking it was nice but afterwards i was left with just cloud. Hopefully next time I'll be able to try the Tiger Eye coffee.

Tip: call ahead to make sure they have the ingredients","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUr21ODJHBU7E4e_64wU4MMONI3mJnfCiETkq5&fid=0x0:0x6a25d042660e3ed3"],"When":"2021-8-21"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Derek Shek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP9Pjija1abf8rOsOgAPBkesWOZ8sALAjyQJKt0I-DTaykDkHV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Prado Cafe is a great spot with plenty of breakfast options to choose from. The iced Americano is strong and flavorful, not too light like in many other cafes, which I really appreciated. The best part is the spacious and comfortable seating area, with power sockets available at most seats—perfect for working or relaxing. It’s a great place to unwind and enjoy a relaxing morning with good coffee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5KBShskJE8amnw-zX4YOI8G8bl33PQJVaW3Yj&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I really liked Prado, coffee was great, food was great albeit a little expensive. Atmosphere is amazing, my only gripe is the limited parking time, 15m is not the longest especially if you want to study. However, other then that I will be back definitely— if they could get longer parking it would be easily one of the best cafes to go to in Burnaby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaGew5ZIHmaGGxO7kCkwdD4KZfiP1c6EEm5WuY&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Mory M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPs8avgpY6Oe_Ytsg4rqTPRpKj-6YZ9I59NE5Wd6hmPPMEz98=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow!
I was blown away by the expansive space and professional ambiance at this coffee shop. From the moment I walked in, I felt welcomed by the sleek and modern decor. The spacious layout provides the perfect environment for both productivity and relaxation. The staff's professionalism and attention to detail truly elevate the experience. And let's not forget the coffee - it's exceptional! Whether you're looking for a quiet spot to work or a stylish setting to catch up with friends, this coffee shop exceeds expectations on every level.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5NttlC5uvOzFpPNO6uunO05lU75BHgNEewRI&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Melinda W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqFa91nGQX9-WVxFZ-rAUul10GF70bhWZFQZe97ymoPVUZrvFxnA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came to Prado with my husband based on the reviews on Google, despite its costly pay parking. Why? I'd like to experience the quietness and spaciousness praised by the reviewers.

Indeed, Prado is quiet and spacious to say the least. I can easily spend a whole afternoon or day here with a coffee and a book if I'm willing to pay the expensive parking fee, LoL. The coffee and sandwiches tasted good, and the sitting area is very comfortable with lounge chairs and work chairs. Electric sockets are also conveniently located everywhere for laptop users.

I would have given Prado a higher rating if it has free parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbhEgi31PmmWQ-7dU1BN1zjok4CC8BVn_xgNev&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"Pearl Rose von Euw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBzQjzzGHsxkUQyewt440jrpJ1s9xIXESPk355K3n1sZzmjq2Suw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Unexpected place to find a Prado but glad it's here! On the first floor of a large, new office building. We visited after an appointment at the hospital because I already know I love Prado's vegan baked goods! Had the apricot cookie and an oat milk cappuccino. The seating area is for the whole building, and is very spacious and comfortable, similar to a fancy hotel lobby. Big windows, outlets and lots of different kinds of seating. Would be the perfect place to study or work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOa_uudXYbz0iwv1yCyW2bg3-wLAl_I0f6qnRct&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"Kingramen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU35K9K-3WDR1LhMOarmobzfUiY3qJQT45Dn4vfHiWAkp32qFPGKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nicely tucked in the foyer of an office building, spacious and plenty of seats. Bake goods and coffee were reliable. Only 15mins free parking, wish the paid parking is cheaper so that I could enjoy my coffee longer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZynVEzg7nEgkSykIuphyE3PMc7gD2KVSUfOI-&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2024-6-5"},{"Name":"Varsha Nageshkar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh8UYpVWUHsqi7LMicpGtUyq9iH1BXWFJXG5AdxKyzvCufqscf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This has to be my favourite Prado Cafe of all locations! That feeling of space, luxury, architecture and divine coffee when you enter and that first sip (there were also some firemen getting their to-go’s - so believe me when I say it was a complete experience - LOL 😉).
Expertly pulled coffee shots with it’s silky oat milk texture! Their ham and cheese croissant was a winner too - it had a very unique sauce inside that made it apart from the rest!
Would love to come here everyday 🤍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRftOd4d-tzH0CfTbFP1FBYZdTBrm8XwZH8vtb&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2023-4-7"},{"Name":"Abhay Verma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrV_6i4dbcDuraV7ft63f2m_fuGbXlt4ooiSAA_Az5gxTkAzw0Lg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Discovered this one almost by accident.

In a building with a bunch of offices, Prado cafe has a huge area for sitting, well spaced and colorful, creative spaces. They have a individual rooms for teams to sit and talk and work while getting coffee ☕, and it seems like a great atmosphere.

The cookie with no name seems to be made entirely of bran / coconut, which can be shocking if you're not prepared for it","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhTPi-_uhDfYYcHNjNXOrczEpCKd1Nz0sA4uAf&fid=0x0:0x2aeccdc42f75902"],"When":"2023-3-9"}]

[{"Name":"Penny Rusty Sophie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkGfXMIDqwS_yD1axTk6tkHoLsnybE2ErvKrHMoMIElMJWekI_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the half n' half from Chicko Chicken with original and soy garlic boneless chicken. The fries here are pretty good with a nice crispness.

Between the two varieties we tried, I preferred the soy garlic because it had better flavor but both were juicy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKKabQiL7s7wk9ss9X7WCM5Fe--dbeSulV4G6_&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Vinn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQu8OcZEY_ggYCVIWaGP71PxsxB9bFIrKDpCQZJQT8VzP7SYcq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So I'm a regular at Chicko Chicken and because of my work, I travel regularly around metro van. I ordered a full boneless Original and the chicken was really greasy after a few pieces. Their fryers were really dirty too. Tasted like I was eating KFC but a version that was somehow worse. I would not recommend this location unless they cleaned their oil. Also chicken looked slightly overcooked as if the oil was overused and/or fryer temp was too high.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiDeY8cMNZm0L_eAEe96mb1BjjZ5xur1T8f7vO&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I find their yang yeom to be the most tasty out of all the korean chicken places but their portions are also the smallest and their price is higher.

I got a half half. This is supposed to be a full size but there are not a lot of pieces and the pieces are small. Yang yeom was delicious as always and juicy. The original was much drier. I think KnC still wins in portion and original chicken.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEhffp1OJtbzoaU359o4B0PH9EjOTre05LQinM&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Alyssa Alexandera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV95VpKh_Tdijxwf_FmdOEYfNLTLHWEG3UIMyC3BunlgTP-0qg-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My main issue is the cleanliness of the establishment. It’s very very dirty. We have found a used condom wrapper on the floor before. Months, maybe years of grime has caked up on the walls, floors, and doors.I keep coming back to see if they’ll clean it but it’s been almost a year and it just gets worse. Photos included to show what I mean..

The workers are very friendly and helpful, especially a younger Asian male that works there whose name I couldn’t see. He is always so positive and helpful.

The chicken is ok although my partner who had worked in a kitchen for many years said they fried the food in old oil and it tasted as such. But I still like the food honestly.

They just reallllly need to clean up and clean that fryer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7QqDQKnyQNMy0PTIwA5esuelB1_Q7JXZxa7hd&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Evelin F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlpccWGsbbpWl4eBYWEt9MHgHiw1EbO9GpMWjL2hPb9w0F9MX3Og=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"While visiting Vancouver I decided to try this place out despite the bad reviews. I wholeheartedly regret it. I got the half original and some fries. The chicken was dry and chewy in some parts. They should at least offer some dipping sauce. The fries kinda had a bitter after taste maybe from the oil. I immediately got sick and threw up after eating this food (no joke). I am in my bed feeling extremely sick. I do not recommend this place at all. It’s probably the grossest fried chicken I’ve tried. Also, they claim that it’s Korea style chicken but there is nothing Korean about the chicken. At least the one I got. I regret spending my money here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZzBZwZAsCzTCLDg0jKofAFswbgPXjyfU8M0Lr&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2022-8-14"},{"Name":"Vinz T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlf4UX6_X5QccNE_C6bW6QyYxUtcav7aSLcQJKbJdCk8R_OgGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Korean-style fried chicken pieces sold here have intense flavours; both the spicy and the cheese taste delicious. The chickens are still crispy even though it has cooled down a bit after we went home. The Half & half set is a good deal if you want to try more flavour at a time.
And I am surprised that the staff can speak Cantonese! I will visit here more often!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMavNje-cMI4xo3hsGir0gl0G6OGr8LoNW5XYWw&fid=0x0:0x22444104e6a0c514"],"When":"2022-6-25"},{"Name":"Kyle White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIL4_HFTLTwyDPEc2QtcdJHZPA-QlFR6D0bYx-TVSy9sWeH8oyx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped here randomly when trying to find some food on the way to the border. The chicken was hot and freshly made to order, super crunchy, and seasoned well. Definitely would like to try some more of the flavors if I'm in the area again!

My only complaint is that it didn't really feel like the place was set up for you to actually eat in there. There was only two small tables, no restroom, no trash, and no utensils or napkins were provided without asking. It was more like a takeout counter.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isabelle Tao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw2KGTF-sTQi7Ul-L7YBNjbpkTwzuGJ-5gy33iiL9ZPmSBUg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Avoid this place—it’s a complete scam. I placed an order through Uber Eats but canceled within a minute after realizing I’d selected the wrong delivery address. Despite canceling immediately, I was still charged the full price. Both the restaurant and Uber Eats refused to issue a refund. So, I ended up with no food and still got charged. Terrible experience!","Images":null,"When":""}]

I ordered a BLT sandwich which took 10 minutes to make, others who ordered after me with more complex orders and orders with more items came out before mine, when they finally gave me my order the bacon was RAW,  I showed the employees what I was served and they were making up excuses. I’ve worked in the food industry for a long time and would not be proud of serving a meal with RAW bacon. 0/10","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaRnU0Z4mnrGgCpyBvuOd9Zp_JN_q6jk9Mg42J&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"alice w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfBFd5-MCz0iWhHQjADA6mFZoHPhSAyoSlVDQe971OUgYbxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Is awesome services 👏  good promotion and points 😋I come back because her she is so understanding and patience","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPlQE1jBjU2NTiYdfzziHZ5n0lgfjJOmDtGZYq&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Onkar Soni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnXpnSLlJdNfEKG8uW6dPFVdt_Lp2exx1ij70Zg51BnWM2K-o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This location of Tim Hortons is amazing. The staff is really nice and quick. Their customer service also amaze me every time with fresh food and beverages. I have been visiting this location from last couple of months for buying steeped tea and every time they serve freshest. 👍🏻","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"PS Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_g_HTUMcwnap-6Tqsuys0sImUj6xffP3fel-XaM9cPLchwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Orders 2 ice caps & 20 timbits. Cashier was ok. However, the timbits picker was rude. Told her I didn’t want colour-dotted timbits & to pick the bottom ones including the no sugar ones but she picked it anyway. She realized it later when I reminded her, she literally shouted at me saying she got it & took out the coloured dotted ones. When I got back to the office, there were 19 instead of 20, and part of one had broken off into 2. Also, there was no sugarless timbits!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrLkRpBYlisxAlrMd7n8FZiUgFIyoFYCmmnsu6&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Conner Forseth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuyyAn6tMsFhsn5l6GGfpBkZYCMVcaYNKX_-I0-chy-QMVldjS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today was my last straw with this place. I ordered online and they gave me the wrong order, i go back to exchange it and they offer zero apology and just look annoyed. I ask for light sauce and they still don't listen. 15 mins of my break wasted. I order here once a week and the team here consistently messes up on orders and the customer service is non existent. They just glare at you like you are an inconvenience. This location needs serious help...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv2lCQagJGNS8AgIYCbU5mC_iTObSM6anRNRLQ&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2024-5-29"},{"Name":"Aliia Lolieva","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRz6jwxUt32yZqWVv8qsVv7NB8upN_oDHsa5DhVBXfApBmVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was disappointed with the donuts I purchased on Saturday, August 3. While cutting one of them in half, I noticed something wrapping around my knife. Upon closer inspection, I realized it was a long piece of plastic. The kids were disgusted by it, and we were just thankful that a child didn’t end up eating it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpbW2iBILuibuqurau5GxbQij858b4Oniu2Oza&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Pascal Gagnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqkHj9YGg9N-z1gv_gRFjSBKIYi6kus3PBF4HROcZduF7gOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went to the Tim Hortons, second floor,  at 7:55 pm on Monday (Dec 9th) ordering coffee for my crew (night shift).
We are from our of town here for the last 4 weeks. Working 6 days a week.

Order our usual 3 large coffees, one medium dark roast coffee and a large tea plus whatever else we get for snacks , to be told that I would have to wait 10 minutes for the coffee!!!!

This is a coffee shop!!!!

Can't we think ahead!?!?!

I was able to get a dark roast once in the last month from that shop!
I lost it to the manager of that shop.

He barred me and I am proud!!

This Tim Hortons doesn't deserve my money nor my crew's money.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Munim Chowdhury","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWE8TBJz0hTcBIVBwK1uPUDqd4mCQH8f8v47uBJOZWw27pK1Clk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Your regular Tim Hortons in Metrotown. We had Tim Bits, Chocolate Croissant, and my favorite French Vanilla. The waitresses were very friendly and served us well. The washrooms were out of service, which is a downside. Also, there is a very limited number of seating space and is almost always occupied, therefore if you want to sip on your coffee peacefully, this may not be the place. This is perfect to get your on the go coffee and munchies.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX1T6xBK4PoKo0GBOi0nvoegjco0QCyIBVNhLQ&fid=0x0:0x77f2ff61c08a5b34"],"When":"2023-4-24"}]

[{"Name":"Richard Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGQIzuskChalQPFAYkJyekOzVkgo_Xf7cxqW4S7hHcUirWNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Let me set the stage for you: it was a rainy Thursday at Metrotown Mall. My hunger was ferocious, and the enticing aromas of sizzling teriyaki lured me into the siren’s trap that is Koya Japan. Little did I know I was about to embark on a culinary nightmare so profound, Gordon Ramsay himself would weep.

The line moved slower than a glacier, as though each customer before me was hand-forging their teriyaki dreams from scratch. At last, it was my turn. I ordered a Chicken Teriyaki Bento—a safe, classic choice, or so I thought. The price? A staggering $14.95. For that price, I expected a taste of Mount Fuji itself.

The first red flag? The chicken looked like it had fought valiantly in a grease war and lost. It was drowned—no, submerged—in teriyaki sauce so syrupy and overwhelming it could have doubled as engine oil. The vegetables were limp, lifeless, and tasted like they’d been resurrected from last week’s compost pile. And the rice? A soggy blob that clung to my fork as though it feared the outside world.

Ah, but let’s talk about the “tempura,” if we dare call it that. The batter was a soggy, oil-soaked crime against all things crunchy. Each bite felt like chewing on a damp napkin. The shrimp? A whisper of protein lost in a sea of grease. I could feel my arteries pleading for mercy.

As I sat there in the crowded food court, staring at my meal like a tragic Shakespearean hero surveying the ruins of his life, I noticed something curious: the staff, moving with the urgency of sloths on a coffee break, were haphazardly slapping together orders. Quality control? Nonexistent. Passion? A distant memory.

I left Koya Japan not just disappointed but personally offended. Offended that this establishment dares to peddle such lackluster meals in one of Canada’s busiest malls. Offended that I spent $14.95 to feel betrayed. My stomach churned with regret, and my soul yearned for the innocence I had lost.

To the brave souls considering Koya Japan: turn back now. Go anywhere else. Heck, eat at home. The culinary gods will thank you, and your wallet will too.

One star—and that’s only because zero stars isn’t an option.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcFXLI0fHSydf5iCK8407MQGzii8eGDtxqjqTe&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Michael Kashkov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHQqdkZ8UrMNX3JXJAPLi5tzL0seRzCv7BAbjOzZvIyrXvPY1SuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot believe that I still can get a decent portion of ramen for approx $12 and not be hungry afterwards. The price is reasonable, the service is actually good! The cashier girl was nice and helpful, the Chef was fast, the food was tasty. What else would I wish? It's a shame that they don't have a location somewhere in downtown, I would be a regular customer..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kent Thai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJPalwxa1xkrH90Zp2w57yH3MhFFl41K6kDSHqolk-e_Uzs0VI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst chicken yakiudon (stir fry) I've ever had. Served only a few pieces of chicken with so little veggies. Teriyaki sauce was so salty. Not recommended. Take your money to eat somewhere else like U Grill or Bourbon, they cook better food with better portion","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kab Kbaas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5U0xr3upvQTURbvXCvcu5mgHu9kAs3kt9vv_C4iuqaE8mdtRkEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We enjoyed our first visit to this restaurant located at the food court in Metrotown. The food was flavourful, mushrooms were apparent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEsCIO5lnWj1gxYkbq_JGkAoZNWDnkQeJC6Ec4&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Maryam BG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYOocnrrI0wz1xy1UzzrfX002uyW86PfiNNhxdXyfBusTbUhlS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the chicken udon and it was good, nothing too special. The vegetables were mostly cabbage and the chicken was teriyaki style. The broth was a bit too salty and lacking depth.

The customer service on the other hand was amazing and nice, and the pricing is reasonable for the udons","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN29kIEMvVbunmZWY-XQdDr338x2QO_8Y_xFcwq&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2022-12-4"},{"Name":"Thomas Lian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfz5QG3NX75tOmniF2dyXqZfzIGVE7s88fet2F00TVL0Vye9dV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great smell, good staff and great visuals are all things you will find in this restaurant. I ordered 200oz fountain drink, chicken teriyaki classic and curry Japanese style and what a treat! I once tried a curry I loved more than anything in the world and after trying many restaurants I was never able to find one like it, until now! Their Japanese style curry is the best I’ve tasted, with not too strong smell, decent taste and expectable portions. Their chicken teriyaki was one of the better ones I’ve tried. Decent smell, mediocre tasting broccoli, but great chicken. I was going to go to A&W’s today but I decided to try something new and I looked at the one that stood out to me most. Overall I will definitely (if I can remember) come here again. I would (to the highest possible degree) recommend coming here if you are looking for quick, great, grilled food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiGTLnhiAJOAyeeGfctN8L-Qlz5yg7q2ALCRXS&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2018-9-21"},{"Name":"Ada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_tT85lO7aZKFfq17wWpo8ldgI_n0GJFJfBhG1nWiEa2zXCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered a beef udon take out and they gave me a plain udon. I only realized when I got home. I tried to call them during work hours several times and they didn't pick up at all. Hope they will rectify the situation when I go back and tell them in person. The Chinese woman in charge of taking the order was also very rude and said she wouldn't separate the soup "when they are busy" even though it's takeout. She gave me attitude when I requested soup and udon to be separate so it won't be soggy by the time I get home.

Addendum: I came back during a weekday morning and the Korean man and lady (who seemed to be the owner) is much nicer and kept apologizing and gave me a beef udon as replacement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5OZncBKDL3gfOyB_ghoTsNAp8QEmy-EgpuGEZ&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2023-11-27"},{"Name":"Dr. Tse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1c97-meBhhJqxDvPj4fmZwUaEh_PPmcuc2SOSOUOWDAGqU11h8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We enjoy going to Koya, always cooking in front of you, fresh food which you chose the different combos! Very polite staff!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0oEeZ5Hj6_6FBy3f1Xi84Z_gr7f9OhUrJPvhU&fid=0x0:0x47770b74a4caa896"],"When":"2022-5-31"}]
