[{"Name":"MJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlm_XRYtoUIMsDe0r0YhYfxDQnj37a3FGprKGl2_zxeQCNP_XX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The atmosphere here is just so lively and amazing, full of botanical plants and just great vibes!

However, as much as the atmosphere was amazing, I wasn’t too happy with the quality of their food. I ordered a margarita pizza, as our server recommended. The pizza was lacking some flavour and was weirdly very chewy by texture.

Perhaps, next time I can try a different dish and give birdies another chance. Would definitely return for the environment and atmosphere✨.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvTUbQT3MVU2zFnYTr-Daj8eIa2M9eJyDa_7eA&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Fuzzy Nemo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhjGNDhI-RZYgIiVRXnRDEQCiyyP-dsVjb7EhBkcymNr9MvYi0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have seen a few posts about this place when it first opened and seems to be quite positive,  so just wanted to give it a try.  This was the old location of Earls Lougheed and they have changed up the decor and have a little section for takeout.

We were here for happy hour.  We ordered:
- Fish Tacos $6.75 each, which were one of the better ones that we have had.
- The Forager Pizza $15.75, highly recommend.   This pizza surprised us, it was so good and it was a lot of pizza for they price
- Birdies Wings $15.75, was meh and in comparison, this was a very small dish for the price.  Not worth ordering again.
- Guava Berry Fizz $7.50, came in a very tall glass, tasted great and presentation was cute
- Culture Blueberry Ginger Kombucha $9.75, it was served in the can, which we didn't know and felt that it was extremely overpriced.

Service was great.  Sam was very attentive and extremely friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuoKeLdzvaRYISOKbL97krNqQWsgJ3zJRhPh4p&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Daniel Vasquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfH4IGtDH-RZPfkWL0P5tVuSs9PJ8oLSHVNJs_o3NyG6_oaSvUng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant and the atmosphere are great, fantastic setup and patio with fun music; a good spot for a dinner party, drinks, etc. I would rate this a 4.

The service was fine, not poor, not great; a 3 for sure. As for the food I would have to give it a 2.5; the presentation was awesome however the flavour lacked and it was consistent for every meal with the exception of their pizza. I would rate the pizza a 4.

I would go back for drinks and pizza only.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNT119sK6afvpHr7WEueY1XPVMvOs9mXk8qwiGa&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a satisfying early dinner here. This is Earls' 'California' concept, and it definitely had a different, more funky vibe than your typical Earls. Solid Happy Hour menu. The margarita (on the rocks, freshly-squeezed lime) was excellent. Fish taco was great, with a sizeable piece of fish, not greasy at all. Forager pizza was excellent, with really nice flavours of mushrooms & kale. Will be back to try more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOX_u_01h0NQmSLdPsryJ2x-y0IPrJnOp3FD9ix&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Marley Mckenzie cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5n4XAwgV26WrtDQFOwKexjEHrP8ok0rq2RztGWysEOnM29r4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been meaning to try birdies for quite sometime but always forget about it when the time comes. Last night coming back from pumpkins after dark we stopped and had dinner and it was very good! The unholy guacamole was so good, lots of good flavours! Service was good and the atmosphere was good but the music was a little bit loud but understanding it was later on at night. 100% recommend this place for lunch, brunch or dinner!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqsk5CbWE9UmadjuFqP68lur9paynVs3VwgJk&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"G P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRBH3kmEC7zS9DCguHUR7BLkUesLTmOGdsJIgTl4hlmh9fnA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I recently went to Birdie's for a lunch date with friends. The food was enjoyable, my friends tried the fried chicken sandwich, while I opted for the prawn and scallop paella. We also shared the Birdie's wings and the crème brûlée cheesecake. The wings were decent in flavor but lacked meatiness. However, the crème brûlée cheesecake was the standout, it was absolutely delicious and worth a return trip just for that!

While the food was satisfying overall, the service left much to be desired. Our server was notably slow, taking a long time to take our order and bring the bill. We ended up spending almost two and a half hours there, mostly waiting for our server to check on us. I had to wave them down repeatedly, and it was only when a different staff member noticed that I got any attention. The restaurant wasn’t particularly busy, so I’m not sure why the service was so delayed.

I wanted to actually tip less because of the service, but I just that the lower option of the tips which was 18% and regret because it wasn’t even worth that.  Overall, I’d come back for the food, especially that cheesecake, but don’t go in expecting stellar service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJMFfD6seNxI7cNcUKss2odI7uYWCGpzSif9ed&fid=0x0:0x2b0126a7cf1b7ba3"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"John Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnQcmQk5zXvH68j5FJSO-DZt_bNb-sv4XDWST0oWFFOK2Ke2-Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This meal for 2 cost us $70, would you pay that? We were expecting a bit more quality for the price. The $23 “tacos” had no filling except meat, and the plate of spaghetti and shrimp cost $26 alone. Not worth it.

The service was ok and the restaurant was nice but a bit loud. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kobe Szeto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlXFS7K5cf4oaXh5NbPybJ77PXSSgQ37mCOmvpLuaHRJFrQI4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very happy with our experience here despite my dad being hit on the head by their patio umbrella…🤭

We were seated outside due to our larger party and it was a super windy day. They had their patio umbrellas open despite there being no sun. Suddenly, the patio umbrella gets blown over and strikes my dad on the head quite hard while we were waiting for our food. He’s in shock and his head hurts quite a bit, he even got a small bump. They quickly closed the umbrellas and apologized.

My dad felt unsafe and he was not able to enjoy his experience sitting outside because he was afraid the umbrella would come crashing down again. We kindly request to be moved indoors and we didn’t mind sitting separately as well. Management and servers quickly and kindly accommodated us into one table and apologized profusely. They handled the situation with grace and professionalism which we really appreciated! They continued checking in on us frequently to make sure we were okay (even offering ice for my dad). Scott the manager was extremely understanding and apologetic, he handled this situation extremely well and offered a free meal next time we visit! We understand accidents happen so we are grateful they were able to help us feel safer during our experience at OEB! We appreciate the great service and food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPd2C7cf-D_hw263JEdDHJgf_Xd48At9IZWO4z&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"OEB Breakfast Co is worth the hype! The Tuna Crudo Breakfast Poutine is my favourite dish. It's fun, delicious, and satisfying.

The food isn't heavy while you're eating it, but all that tallow catches up on you 🤭 Enjoy the warm vibes and fantastic food.

OEB is one of my favourite spots for brunch in Burnaby. But do yourself a favour: join the online list to avoid waiting for a table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjEe-c98X2E3Rg5zcVG8YMNFa8G8jKabnrzIPJ&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHTcuSM-4ly1uIP3q2-jgQ_2Vqi7GhBmGO9JykCcOlnN1NYOmqYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely a place you want to show up early for - it gets busy! We arrived around 10:15am on a Saturday and had the luck of scoring bar seating right away; a table wait for 2 was around 45 minutes+. The restaurant has a bright, bubbly and buzzy brunch vibe. Great service and quick turnover. The food was fabulous. I could eat the Blue Crab Benedict over and over again. Cocktails were perfect for brunch, their fancy mimosa with peach and elderflower wasn’t too sweet. Just right!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEcJmRP15kaWYj_Co2bJJGYWJkBuY9CP4CRxAn&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"TGB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUryvg13C_-YoeFueRwWjGtDO91qKkh7JeWoCftKmKv0RdhqW9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The location was pretty convenient, the wait staffs are friendly and nice. The food was pretty decent 8/10. We ordered a lavender latte (I highly recommend this) and 2 poutines. The poutines were good and they let you have the option of choosing all potatoes or potatoes with veggies, which is awesome for people like me who usually couldn’t finish their plate at once!! Also I love that we can join the waitlist online beforehand so you can plan your time around it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXI94wMHO-BfcIlKH-6V43VEivaN8wEIlwWGZc&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"JT James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU161kQr0_4muVDKJU6-gjT33fWLEyByh4-HEo8sil4hm3gbcR_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t say enough about this place.  They should hire me for their PR team as I’ve been championing this place for the last month since I discovered them, dragging all my friends here.

Hands down the best diner/breakfast restaurant around.  The food is impeccable but still the same price you will pay at your regular breakfast spot.   Service is always great.  Cozy modern and clean atmosphere.  5/5","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOI0wahaewT10kROox0wECxjL4hhFK27il-xfGk&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"pooja acharya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgwR7H53zquGvLTQQ-SjiVtHJhthL-hppRhXuKcdAxii_L7zk8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was delicious; it is the busiest place. The service was friendly and the food was delicious. I appreciated the server taking his time to explain some the ingredients they use and their cooking methods. My sister and I shared the smoked salmon benny and the brioche french toast. We opted for the roasted potatoes instead of the crispy ones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_Yc-hE6476ufyYIDLu9ZdcS4prww4_6anVslq&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Chris T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyH2CqrRQT9WQ4FPQHoAcosEs8JVj-45uQVURp3XpjMFPLhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to OEB with my family and found out they just came out with a new menu. Will be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpILWhRDTQj9LZ3nIBTdpXmd5KQ_J6R_FTTTLx&fid=0x0:0x706ecd309abb2ee1"],"When":"2024-11-13"}]

Worth the walk over. Sadly does close relatively early because of the class schedule for the building. Okay poutine, actual cheese curds. Good Sandwiches. Sometime the waits are long because this place seem understaffed because of people coming from other parts of the campus.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Spirit G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWA5aGSbjNcsLqQnTBLuNPVGLjNOTV6t9zmSXEKBdX3dinaSOE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I have gone to bcit for 3 of my four years of apprenticeship, and this cafe used to be great!  They had good food, prices, and fast service.  And while the staff are doing an amazing job pushing the current place to 150%, the management decisions that brought it to where it is now, were clearly awful.  The food prices have gone up on average of two dollars since last year, while also shrinking the portion size by almost a third.  The quality of product has also fallen sharply.  There are two active lines of food here, one for Tim Hortons express, and the other for the grill, but management has apparently closed one of the two tills, forcing everyone to go through the grill checkout from the beginning of the grill line, even if you just wanted a coffee.  This negates the value of an express line, and was not a problem before the \"upgrade\".\nNow the head chef lady, who has been working there forever, doing a great job cooking good food, is tethered to the only till, while her colleagues scramble faithfully to keep up.  This is not a fault of the staff, but rather, the management.  Merciless cost cutting is to blame.  If management were to push the cost cutting any further, this establishment would likely become profit negative.   If you give experienced, dedicated staff low quality products to serve, without the proper tools to succeed, and actually expect high quality food that will create customer satisfaction, you are blind on both sides of the coin.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Axel Galay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJW4X_1eFL5Ne9l9qxkKyX_NP2g2CtUIWPCBopINNILV4oGWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food here is overpriced and pre cooked under a heat lamp. The food here is NOT good only saving grace is coffee but it's already Timmies coffee","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Connor R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdiGt2Hea6RfRjwMquYQMMBahuHfegX1L0VeHIH61OrWE70WgQpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Used to have great tasting, well priced breakfasts but after they redecorated/changed its terrible.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Daria Liukin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkJyqUukJ1Tp32CT1Y60hgwO8TEu98t8UrHjC4vSHU3XhtZR-hfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited Tap & Barrel right after it opened for brunch, and the place is amazing! It has three floors—the first and second are indoor and open year-round, while the third is a patio open during the summer. We sat on the second floor, right by the windows overlooking the Brentwood fountain, and the view was beautiful!

The service was excellent, with super friendly staff who welcomed us warmly, shared details about the restaurant, and answered all our questions with big smiles and great energy. The waiters helped us choose our dishes, explaining everything in detail.

The food was delicious, and we were completely full afterward. Overall, we loved everything and highly recommend this place!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPqCHdmfT_Zut7ya0BhtYUwwB2igZ_ntEpRaoV&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Elise Coulombe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViK4jjoo4e0IQVt9oYUgRxEQZAEfBII2krEdtoehaUBKGdHAcJQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Robyn was amazing! Such a sweet server and made our time there fantastic!

We ordered the Valentina honey lettuce wraps not knowing what to expect and they were absolutely delicious. I want them catered to my wedding. Also ordered the prosciutto and arugula pizza which was delicious as well. Great experience here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWE5aWqSYChj83-B81rpc9eGbA33zQFnrtdvbM&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"toffy concepcion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYhf6f6Tr-b7ekbkXxFz9ueDreb1BCkopv3RQXbcpm54DeMfYl5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is an excellent Tap and Barrel with really friendly and helpful staff from the start to finish. While trying to avail of the free parking from the app. Aaron the bar tender saw me struggling and helped me get it done. Yes the bar tenders are always experts. Our server Kelly was really helpful and attentive to our needs. The onion ring burger with truffle fries is excellent. Chicken strips, Salmon, Mac and cheese, loaded nachos were all wonderful and the desserts were great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqq_MDf-GmThYSDGdm4uXn82Aql5JXAHLWyeoV&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"J. Adano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXS6fYBp1czglx2bGTTrcfG3fTSHEuBmlqY6u1JHeL0TPZEijc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had reservations on a Saturday at 6PM. Although it was pretty busy we were seated within 10min of our arrival which was by the window on the second floor. The Canucks game was playing and there were ample TVs around  to watch the game in the background while socializing . Our waitress was very nice and attentive to our needs however, you can tell that she was running around most of the night due to her having multiple tables with large groups. A couple of missed drink orders but totally understandable. We ordered the following appetizers to start: truffle fries, hot wings, lettuce wraps, fresh guacamole and chips. All were good and as expected. For the mains, we all order the 10oz ribeye steak. Everyone agreed that it was tasty and a good sized portion however I found mine a bit salty and garlicky. I would definitely order it again but would request the creole butter on the side. Hence only the 4 stars. We had lots of drinks that were top notch. Started with a few Russel Honey Lager beers to kick things off. Tried a Backcountry Widowmaker IPA which was pretty good as well. Then tried a couple of different cocktails. The ones I’d recommend are the margarita slush, and purple reign. Finally capped it off with desert which I’d highly recommend not skipping because the cheesecake and Affogato ( a scoop of vanilla ice cream and a shot off espresso) were pretty darn good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhf-ST2zJNpIcKBGo9JI_nXupYyAZQ31laQM6X&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Nathan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULis9x-C7u8jouJ6bmV-m7Mb2r-esn5uJaOqGwjwAA9z2MADUV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food took awhile to come and in the end it was alright. The pizza was decent along with fries however the burgers weren’t anything too special unfortunately. Happy hour prices are good which I cant complain. I’ll do my best to come by again as I believe it could’ve just been a bad day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2V7eWzqTRaNFW1w0rwzGnnKvcI6bJpHWetuCO&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"D D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn-HmKGkiEXpPYEJdaFnX-Wk9npBuMky8Sv8ZSJcapzQOOPiN3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Impressive 3 floors with totally different vibes.  Happy hour food was great other than the pizza which was on the bland side.  Service was attentive and friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZOh15bkHbCx7BHK2b7QnwpQvA8LVOVUc-YlW4&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Austin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHuK0QOCQL1j7GL8vaEyrkRaAQrMd6cRbcQduQoDAVviqZGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Took my girlfriend out for our two year anniversary. Upon arrival the host greeting was good but quick, not much talking, no notice about the notes of the anniversary. As someone who works in this industry I was expecting by leaving a note about this special occasion that maybe something more than just regular service would happen sadly it didn’t. Server was nice and friendly, she was on point with her service aside from the dessert, a kid walked to the wrong table with our dessert from afar and then went away, came back 3 minutes later and the ice cream was completely melted all over so we sent it back. When server Ashleigh came by she asked what happened I explained and it was a quick ok and walk away which wasn’t the worst thing in the world just wasn’t the service I was expecting as I thought it was a new restaurant similar to cactus earls etc. key notes I can say. Our server was still very kind and took care of the dessert off the bill, the only main disappointment was no recognition of the special occasion. I wanted to take her originally downtown to five sails but when she suggested we try a new place out I agreed and I put the reservation in hoping the notes would make it a bit more of experience. The food itself was good. The truffle waffle fries were hot and crunchy which we loved with the truffle dip. We had the fish and chips, a bit too battered, barely any fish, prawns are good though. Spicy margarita was good and so was rum and coke. Overall a 3:5-4/5 experience","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSeItj073bnkD9MjCBEqS10INL-cOODSfhuGt1&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Stacy Purum Jeon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJokIsJGL-fv0gSK_iI4jQxVk_jmrb_b6s-LN0DAYOqzSpY2xQLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is ok. But the atmosphere was really fantastic. You can hear the water fountain right in front of the store, and patio was really good.
One thing I had small complaint was it was a little hard to get prompt service. Just because there were not enough servers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzuFvIS_3YMTw1uW-HCwptsL8CIbH-QKCJr9FU&fid=0x0:0x26d644e7075a79b3"],"When":"2024-8-15"}]

However, the quality of the food was quite average considering the amount we paid. The presentation of the food was nice, but the taste was very ordinary; it didn’t have any special or delicious flavor at all. Steak was not cooked professionally. I wouldn’t go there again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMhaz6YjIzlE5U7J-Ly3IwRnM-k9bVo0hG1nHK\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Charlane Binga-An","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBC9x-_wILXUDdwq01M8C9qxZsjtqoem4o9PPBCIkxE_LlhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best Earl's I've been to. The location and atmosphere were great and our server Ben made everything 100% better. He was so friendly and very attentive! We were out celebrating a friend's graduation and he even came out with dessert on the house! It was so sweet of him.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlgTYjVnS6k44h-O8zZUMKHVCtDPwgfUDN7UlM\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Tony Hoang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6S-doEAxjVwXEsWxNgTYzGuqUx22Qq5Y_HPrsxGPh1v6wA7RA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a night out with friends and family the other night. Food was great and steak came medium rare, just how I asked. Plating could have been better but the food tasted great. Nice location and good dining atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNV7PrpJh77mVjy1ZVO1gLNO6g_m9N7c0wK14MK\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-11-7"},{"Name":"D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvU4HdlESptkRf0TqiLSNamp-b3hLIhsTk4jU9jft7nopM4PaG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don’t normally go out to eat, much less at places like Earl’s, so this was a lovely experience! Me and my friends came in to eat a little while ago and had the best server ever. He helped us choose what we wanted to eat as we are a bit indecisive haha and he was super nice about it. He was so attentive without being invasive and we all enjoyed our meals greatly (food was amazing as well). I would totally recommend this place to any Earl’s fans and if you’re looking for someone who knows their way around the menu to ask for Chase!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9BuNkzvi-cgL94JLpF5YXfKMFqL6ADoK8bpVF\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"L.A. ZONIN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3viQRMbbn0pWxqvjD85DAiZP3lZeqbB825G4RkR5Wep1D96Fc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s always such a pleasure being here at Earls. They never disappoint with their food, drinks, and staff. I’ve been coming to Earls since they first opened last year in early spring, and I must say I’m always leaving the place fully satisfied! Tonight I got to meet a new bartender, Brandon. His bartending skills speaks for itself as I ordered a White Peach Whiskey Sour. Presentation was beautiful and the flavour was fireworks in my mouth. Definitely my go-to drink! And Brandon was delightful! Super kind, talented behind the bar, and insightful at best! If you’re looking for a night out at Brentwood, Earls is the perfect place!\n\nP.S the sushi prawn tacos were SOOO GOOD!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnGRfmUZ7dPVgy52Ex0S_AAIa82Vo46QQWMfdU\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Hiep Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRHHZ7t798igHqhwEObqqiXXBYRe7_vTRRS3-gXG7fOgZlXSH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything was good except for the beef sliders. The slider buns had very little meat in it that all I tasted was bread. And they put horse radish or Wasabi inside which turned me off. The sushi taco was the best, then the crab cake. My wife wants to come back for mainly the sushi tacos! We came here for happy hour and the bill came to $72 not including tip.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoBJmJzW0TudtazRZIGCo5xNlsL8wbZ6OgNXLC\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"abby y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP7hgK8G2WOeres9hsGERbOPIrqtMm6w0MVk2J8sSRUhC7fQCB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Benjamin was an amazing server very cutesy, he had a very cute hair charm on and the gold chain was an amazing touch to his outfit. Not only his style was amazing but he was an awesome server for myself and my friends. We were a large group and he met every need during our dining experience!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1XcidQ1rjViEIkdubu_cRTwgv5R5TBnm8gMMI\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"richard chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIf1neCZqBnJLrk0cTe43Vpuwux4gjmUzrrV78_wxQmqDskDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife had a friend come into town, so we decided to take her out for lunch. Earl's Brentwood is a 10  min walk from our condo tower. It sits right in the heart of Brentwood Plaza, which is a busy hot spot for hanging out, shopping, or eating. It's suggested you make reservations because this Earl's gets very busy. It has a dining area inside and a lounge area plus an outside patio. Inside is nicely decorated with a lot of hanging plants and retro lighting and seating. Its very clean inside.  We were sat down quickly, and our waitress greeted us right away. Lucky for us, Earl's serves a brunch menu till 2 pm, so that's what we ordered. My wife had the egg breakfast while my wife's friend and I had the crab cake benny. All of our food tasted great. The crab cakes melted in our mouth. I really like how they made the sliced baked potato squares. Overall the atmosphere, food and service is tops here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLnAupzLWqyurq21Lm65_HkjSbLS2YkIa06MhF\u0026fid=0x0:0x8506999abb5c4096"],"When":"2024-7-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is delicious and well presented. The atmosphere is nice and clean, but their table setting welcomes only 4 or fewer groups. We went there for dinner as a group of 7 and had to wait by standing by the front door for around 80 minutes. Though there were  tables that could accommodate 4 and 2 people from time to time, they prioritized small groups for those tables. We had to wait until they took us to the only table that could accommodate 7. The place is pretty busy, may be because of delicious food. But we will not consider this place as an option if we have a group of 5 or more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONFEg3mrhvnIt2GQIOvnGNiKbyti5HOFOY2koN&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Completely disappointed. I have tried the other branches and they were okay but this branch in particular was not good. We waited an hour for our food, and even then we had to ask why was it taking so long (it’s not that busy either) and they completely forgot our order!! Thankfully the food came within 6minutes which made me skeptical of its quality… the food as you might have expected was not good either. I couldn’t finish my portion. The portion size was big but the taste was not good, very bland and cold. The takoyaki was mushy and mostly just flour with one piece of octopus. The staff was also not attentive, we tried several times to get the bill but was ignored multiple times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzfsMmwDyuarZTF8-jGIGUUQpy22M1OOyBiauL&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Nick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGjptqH3FdoeLfdSjPWQygL5KEsM_ui4pClg77BekGUD0E-Q_8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the place to go if you want to eat good ramen. I've tried multiple ramen places on multiple locations in and around Vancouver but this is the best place I have ever been to for Spicy Ramen. Drinks were on point and food was really good. Prices are not too crazy. The only downside is you have to wait a while before you can get a table. They have additional sauces on the table which is a nice addition if anyone wants to customize the flavor. I would recommend this place for spice lovers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM02bb1LOuOMA4eTY-sSY0d0mS52tvbBAX2cPS-&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"abeth mendoza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBoYK5OSywpF_1QMFL-3DgcIXMsWAGw5i-JXsDNKZF53X54YRH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We dine at lunch time, The service is good we are waiting for 20mins for the seat in a small place we ordered ramen I love the soup and takoyaki is good but the chicken wings and fried chicken taste like ordinary. Good for kids meals absolutely getting full for the combo. And they automatically charge an 18% service fee for two or more people","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM36tx9Soc354xvYJWyfyUXZuvULPM78ndplbnz&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Alicia C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5FZx59zq_1boLwx6VJi3MNlKYZ3f_bpTKTI_oZju90xHEIRQAGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's not a big place and we were seated pretty close to the next table.

We had the premium red ramen and the Jinya tonkatsu black ramen. Additionally, we had some sides - the Jinya bao, gyoza and a salmon sushi roll. The bao comes in singles so we ordered two (one each). It was a little filling and we could certainly reduce the sides.

Lots of toppings available for the ramen and of course, corn is a must-have for any ramen! I like that the ramen egg came whole instead of it being halved which is usually the case for most places.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP68A3G6OIiU6kO_H4a87_BWwL9jGYOm4YkWnrE&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Amrita Nayak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgJ3b8LMBlPc7G1Rv8sy6cyH33IeJwYGYkw6c-i8ocBKF5odAKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our visit to Jinya Ramen Bar was a wonderful experience! Not only was the ramen satisfying, but the service was truly exceptional.

We were celebrating a friend’s birthday, and our server went above and beyond to make it special. Without us asking, they surprised us with a beautifully presented dessert plate for the occasion. That extra touch made the evening feel so thoughtful and memorable.

As for the ramen, it hit all the right notes. The noodles were perfectly chewy, the broth was steaming hot, and the flavors were rich and comforting. I was recovering from nasal congestion at the time, and this bowl of ramen was exactly what I needed—warm, soothing, and absolutely delicious.

Jinya Ramen Bar combines great food with top-notch service, making it an excellent choice whether you're celebrating or just craving a hearty bowl of ramen. Highly recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYcTHcMpMPhNpDCyOidA1QAdqxBoPE-2ZOgShM&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Stella Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvqyQ2KS_YIN6XYOMkDtQZO2ezjEJLWRODsOzNFIWuIhCYtAL-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the spicy maze-men (a chef's special). I wasn't using any fancy camera to take a photo of it, but yet my photo ended up looking better than their menu photo. I loved the combination of the pork belly chashu, soft boiled eggs, kimchi, and raw onions. Every bite was so delicious! The portion size was just perfect!

I had no complaints about anything. The service was good. The atmosphere was decent. Even better, the washroom was stylish and clean. It may as well have been one of the cleanest public washrooms I've been in this year.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1j5uYuTerZnPytp59SQ5P6qGLfGfA9UKvQBjq&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Alejandra Sánchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXt051hy6gEMXkR86-3Xw80cqEx_9MawHfw61-PI0olAIeczxE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was really good! The ramen is traditional and carefully well done and the prices are reasonables. The service was good but could be better (the waitress took our order around 25 minutes after we arrived).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOz0XLGbkuSf649zNbYyRhSG6yMf3Xf7YMrQDkR&fid=0x0:0x85ad4c9034e2a156"],"When":"2024-8-18"}]

[{"Name":"Vern","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXoBEa2DpCVgJo-G-26vwXXigumr7-aNIbPobMzYUx6xUys_Niz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This coffee shop is a hidden gem! The atmosphere is cozy and inviting, with a perfect blend of modern decor and a laid-back vibe. The baristas are friendly and knowledgeable, though I was a bit disappointed when I was told they don’t accept cash. Not sure what’s going on there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPf18_rmAm_0Cu_eElwI9kg8xnquHVGcMKVk0U4&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Dan Le-Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIU55nGNO-JQ_VFmndfqCAupJibjN8FSOn_gorfXsMI0N6YxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had the strawberry latte, red velvet cake, and a matcha affogato. The latte was quite sweet but overall still good. For the matcha affogato the ice cream was higher quality than expected but what I didn’t like was that the matcha was sweetened so combining with the ice cream made it too sweet. The cake was rich and dense in a good way.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfEEaWrA4wlGKppQSI94LAc53YvSh76RDcYss4&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Maxwell Gawlick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-FQXkip2yse2z3b1RpWO7_R3FWgxjecA_Xas3Rr3fz_mzqOKX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This coffee shop is super cute! Beautiful aesthetic, if a little eclectic (jehova's witnesses bookstore and clock collection?). Lots of space and usually isn't too packed. It's a little hidden in the Hanam Mall area.

Lots of dessert selections. They run out of their few savory items pretty early. Their drinks are really nice, but the prices are quite high--a simple latte is like $8, and if you want a non-dairy milk, that'll set you back another $1.5 or so which is quite a bit. Not sure how much of the food they make in house, but most of it is really nice. Very few vegan options, if any. Service is quite basic and standard, no notes.

Definitely check it out--its one of the nicer shops in the area, and a chill place to hang out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIhLzijInSHeaHacZNLYo6EdqrkNI81LeiSRyT&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2024-4-12"},{"Name":"Kyle Mosonyi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxeTGKVkxyzHvcccVuw1tLSYHtK_ptgeMELKf91-fPI7g80CE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We really enjoyed this place. The chilled out atmosphere. The tasty pistachio cream lattes. And the friendly customer service :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCBYPk5YBY8RlC86LELjjAb6td1SDRUAK7RCR2&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Marjan Sodagar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbeUQ7n7qbMJ2OThg_h-Xdq4j4XJUVbpkuCN0QkHtRIcnDrpUJSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Absolutely love this cozy café! The ambiance is so serene and welcoming, perfect for a quiet escape or catching up with friends. The cleanliness and reasonable prices make it a top spot for me. Highly recommend for anyone seeking a relaxed environment and great value!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0C79FAQq19X9Ii9-fEKcnbOi3eEhfp4N7XNH_&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2023-11-25"},{"Name":"Geun U. Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6SO8lO72UTrTSg7RsdJk__lqfXqluZHM7hskTVFK1sy0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love Standing Egg Coffee! The coffee is incredibly fresh and full of rich flavor – you can really tell they use high-quality beans. The cafe itself is spotless, with a clean and cozy atmosphere that's perfect for relaxing or getting some work done. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Griffin E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWg2Wqa1fy1fYhSFHxSpRb63pjmRObTxWqK25FqTJeees5QOwY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was an absolute surprise! I came later in the evening expecting this location to be one of the more average coffee shops of the region, but the establishment was absolutely fantastic! The staff were incredibly friendly and generous, the coffee was delicious and the sweets were honestly quite immaculate. The music and vibes in the place were very nice and overall I was genuinely surprised at how nice it was, would highly recommend if one needs a place to relax, sit back and either study or work or socialise or simply just to enjoy the coffee!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Girl Reviews","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvDfeBJPT1nj16z6EBMTiqkqgT5efrboX5VoxDUlqzwm9wxZOI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favorite cafes to go to in the KTown area. Their coffee is really good, I normally just get an Americano.
However, the sweet potato latte, and matcha latte are very good as well.

Workers are always friendly, the tables are always getting cleaned up quickly, and a very cute/nice ambience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmU1dRIpzxEYBiIE6-exSejqUADHhFMs0eDTdC&fid=0x0:0x6c2610ba83a35ef0"],"When":"2024-3-4"}]

[{"Name":"Vida Nayeri Laurent","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaZYxHvWD_g4TBrKcc_gTKoe0970q0swxO0SodwKDhNIILjAMoRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michelin star alert ! This place really deserves a star. Everything was beyond our expectations. Fernanda was superb. She was an amazing hostess. We’ve been to couple of Japanese restaurants with Michelin star but this was much better experience at Hello Nori. I really wanted to congratulate you guys for running such a memorable restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORcDdGcw5XvrrzKRfSEXY_qoVAnb98OI5IeFNS&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Tricia C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIS8jxdORXKJaAWhct8yqQ3gE8qhWdlJFJL5jsz8u98jLVDfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fresh seafood serve on fresh crispy seaweed. The warm rice, fresh quality seafood and the extra crunch from the seaweed is what makes this restaurant unique. There are few Japanese restaurants in town that serve this level of crisp seaweed on the spot. Most rolls with seaweed are soft or soggy by the time it is consumed. Staff is welcoming and attentive to customers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaMJ1Xy146NJjpnA6GfblA4K1e-deyRsBxxynH&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Sky Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsnlFBmRy7tyi6QC1WQMYS-_XgUyK7bm7m7BJrwzV_4Y89SkWE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last night, I had a very pleasant experience with great people and delicious food. I could tell they use fresh, high-quality ingredients. I really enjoyed the sashimi platter and the decent selection of sake.

Our server, Shin, was very attentive and passionate, which made our night even more delightful. We stayed until closing time, but the supervisor made us feel very comfortable until we left the restaurant.

I wish I had this place near me!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMklrQKDAuisjxAzciByZQmPezMkPARgledNENo&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"eilian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRs3q9A91UKpxgK5zcvbayckaCDV2p4ClNKRnRX52C5mv0G9p0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great hand rolls, highly recommend the scallop. Unbelievably soft and melted like butter. We got a tuna and salmon sashimi set and it was amazing as well. Feature cocktail was great too. Service was top notch. Got a few things on the house. 10/10 worth the trip","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODFtrVxex_EC-oTn3d9A8bFCXN82TAU6iNaynD&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Michelle Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4pcPjl4t4uNODsq0hbbsjMmM281GvrEzF7xn8jCwVVL-Z2P8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here at Hello Nori and I can say that the food and experience were top notch. I got the 5-hand roll, Nakano (Saika), happy hour zen combo and mochi ice cream. You can taste the freshness/quality in all the hand rolls and sashimi. Of the hand rolls, my favourite were the Hokkaido scallop and snow crab. For the sashimi, sockeye salmon was the one.

All the staff were welcoming and warm, making the experience and transitions in shift-change very smooth.

Special shout out to Maheen & Sam for going above and beyond in giving recommendations and attentiveness in service. This place is definitely worth the price in food, quality, and service.

I’ll definitely have to try out the new location back home (Toronto)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCBFw-KQ3QaQrxozT6jVYNzhQFKiYDEp6NSM0V&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Mark Yun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_DhXmHOWNG6_6L5CabHJeltZVNikmSNa3Wn9EfJqhJfe7Kw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great atmosphere and amazing hospitality from the staff. Hana and Zuzana were both fantastic and really made us feel at home. This was my second visit, and the food was perfect. All the explanations about the dishes made them taste even better. Highly recommend—definitely worth trying if you're into Omakase-style Japanese cuisine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPq9cYSKJpkL1snq9jmXphGu916vT1nwc53GBZ&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Ty Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1elPmigAV5ywdGkLRG-WSJOeq8tpQPGVw0fLYtZMUnFLH6H4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My very first experience with Hello Nori Brentwood was fantastic! The team here was professional, friendly and walked me through the menu with great details. Blake made the whole experience that much better with his professionalism, knowledge and friendly interactions since I was dining in alone. And also thanks to my server—Sam for his spectacular service & attention for all my needs during the experience. I felt welcome and really enjoy my time eating here because of them.

🍣The hand rolls were tasty! I got the top-5 combo which included all of their best-seller hand rolls. Also tried an extra order of Unagi hand-roll as well. Very good!

🍣Sashimi platter was 100% SO GOOD-SO FRESH. Very fresh with premium ingredients. I love that they served fresh wasabi because it really enhanced the freshness taste of the sashimi and doesn’t make your nose feel like it just came out of a boxing match! Presentation was on point. Highly recommend getting this platter to pair with the hand rolls if you can eat more or bring +1.

🍣Salmon Oishi — Smoky, tasty & rich flavours. Definitely recommend!

🍶Cocktail was refreshing. I got lychee berries which was a best-seller. They also have nitrous matcha which I’m excited to try on the next visit! (wanted to order it but was really full at this point.)

🍡Dessert was mochi ice cream. 4 flavours — matcha, vanilla, peach, strawberry. It completed the meal and left me satisfied.

Interior design is modern, unique and definitely a meaning behind the design I’d love to know about it (FYI: each Hello Nori location has a different unique design with the same materials). Overall, was spacious, very clean, good amount of natural light. Loved the music & vibes here.

Price point is very reasonable with the quality of ingredients & services you’re getting from here. Portion will fill you up even though it doesn’t look like it. This visit was my first meal and also my only meal of the day so I was able to eat more than usual😉

10/10 — Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkS39yH9d18k5RrT3YMe7c9i2DwViPTn7Fk5vQ&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-7-23"},{"Name":"Lisa Rugge","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuKeRbC_6lLHCJMThO5S-A_PS8d8NuunLAFT_wCjkZ3Hw_qDE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an amazing experience! The service is phenomenal! Daniella was an amazing hostess who treated us like royalty. The food is beyond fresh and beautiful and so delicious. Sake selections and cocktails are to die for! Can't wait to go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1fCdU1p0rz2Bzx0B3PjBYW1OzciIIpEd58XPA&fid=0x0:0x8e28ab0cee57b8c0"],"When":"2024-9-19"}]

[{"Name":"iriseeks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUN60_e6Ur-2aRAWVagksXHkVjjXJQEtpBqJoH5yb2-dy-4FWWLpg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I highly recommend this restaurant to those who want non fast food options after 8pm. Food is fresh with good quality. The variety of food is amazing. Staffs are very helpful and friendly. Love the atmosphere as well. I know I’m gonna come back!❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNgUkCikURFcEJBFzEAlG4sSTTX0esaLJpTUT-&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Oyako don: I like how the sauce on the rice is sweet and everything feels so smooth that it melts in your mouth.

Chawan-Mushi: caution - it is quite hot when served. Would recommend if you like steamed eggs, and it also includes vegetables, (spinach, mushroom, edamame) shrimp, and ramen flakes. Rich flavours. Well done.

Crème Brûlée Cheese Cake (matcha): I like how it’s not over sweet. It has that cheese cake taste, smooth, soft and yet it is also quite balanced in sweetness. Very nicely done!

Service: my server was very kind to me. Even though the wait was within acceptable range, she felt inclined to apologize for the wait.

Good atmosphere with music playing in the background and people seem to be in groups having an occasional good time.

Thank you Ajishou!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeNjkyngDRLLk4D6fima--pE25nZeSAUMaEaaE&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"PrincessRiccia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIC76C01xrAZ9e-O4ecd02gxPgoXtaGHfTj4U5QIo0wEIwAOA0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really great happy hour menu with a huge variety of items and great prices. Was well worth the value, fish tasted fresh. Service was also good, we will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOliqegrLBm6_zseEDLqu-MR1rbuWdeu3HqMWJ&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place; I've had the most delicious oyster dishes here. Not to mention the sushi—everything is great, and the prices are reasonable. I highly recommend you try it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuF_RpYOikd_eEPYwG-qdF110rroFddz5vpyaa&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"alice w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfBFd5-MCz0iWhHQjADA6mFZoHPhSAyoSlVDQe971OUgYbxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place the food is delicious special after 2:00pm have some appetizers 50%off I have taken some pictures too
The girl have very good service she is patient and polite I have very good services 👍👍🤗The Shrimp and Fried chicken is awesome
Also have many testy rolls etc…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuCpRLE_5tBxqG46s0OGTP_LOmJjalKLyzGAgG&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Emily Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEvwebxzOOvHfn2UnHwr4i_lsQ_4WBBcdmwEUmGOtZoyfwO9Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Nice to have a different choice for Happy Hour deals in that area. The sashimi and the prawn tempura are decent. Service is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoVf6pF4aO7Pf4mOv_PxTCKyTlKWatASCJeE2M&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Kayla Ok","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2ZPW-HOTvhKWxZVs_tiGZng-PPQOf1u70Mg0ytQnqF8DWQ4ac=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not a Japanese run restaurant. Oshi uses siracha mayo typically not used in pressed sushi. Cuts are small and food seems to be dressed up to be fancier and pricier for what it is but many other sushi places are better. Would not eat here again as food is only okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZCgGyiWdMvAaLBj6Pcuof_pnhOOjdaAmASxVP&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Grace Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2Gi0ImD_jtFaRjI_I4TvVHE6110eG-TPY1JG8d59XQJNTtA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came during happy hour on a weekend, no reservation was needed for party of 6. we ordered mostly from the happy hour menu. It offered a good value. I wish they had spicy mayo or some sort of dipping mayo for the chicken karaage and deep fried squid. Sake was also half off $5 for a small size.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOonodQTUJKXO3pvOhoqDG5RgG7S_xh4MfYBQdt&fid=0x0:0x8f1828f7e5f0e899"],"When":"2024-3-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Joanne T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWUm5wApXaGLdrhdyLnYu0BbbvdpiPo1GB0zmazZcIdHhRZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely for a date or hangout with friends. It's a nice difference from the overly dark restaurants that serve similar fare. Staff are friendly and helpful. I appreciated that they were very careful in checking and noting allergies.

Ordered the mussels and clams in white wine cream sauce on two occasions—great flavour and it goes well with the focaccia bread option, but both times there's been sand and some have been super tiny.

Overall nothing particularly standout, but the food is solid!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORU_G8E9nrKWc9Vppz7XeGMjL67RUXWUepXV0T&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Audrey T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVt7NSeCmrDxjN6eGFiHdOku-giePvd1JuUbLyAEp6odBtHY6vv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped by for late night happy hour with some friends. The restaurant is very nice and spacious and service was quick and attentive. I got the sangria and it was tasty. My friends got the house lager and we liked the design on the glasses. Oysters were solid at $2 each. Our first round had a lot of shells, but the second round was perfect. Fish and chips were tasty, and so were the sliders. We preferred the clams over the mussels. We would also skip on the dynamite roll next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNljNi8cXG_PuMKAq_7u9vpwKt0oO3EBbGts70o&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Jessy J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHNRFw0Z_JgaU0TxGr1Pv5X-w9V6JzR0bnCuTDlGr_7pfsbx_k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We dined at Bow & Stern over the weekend as a large party of over 20 people, and the service was definitely the highlight. With four servers attending to us, they were attentive to both the adults and children, providing napkins and handling our requests with care. Although some of the servers seemed new, they delivered the service smoothly, including bringing ice buckets for our wine.

However, the timing of the food was an issue. Despite starting dinner at 6 p.m., we didn’t receive our desserts until around 8:45 p.m. Since it was a school night, we had to pack up and leave without fully enjoying the final course.

As for the food, it was a mixed experience. The mussels should be a must order. I hit one with white wine cream sauce it was superb! The Brussel sprouts were overly sweet. The steak was tough, and the Arctic char was dry with underwhelming crispy skin, and I found a chipped shell in one of my oysters. On the bright side, the risotto and king crab were quite enjoyable, though cracking the King crab leg was a challenge, and the lobster initially lacked butter, which the server kindly provided upon request.

Overall, service was the standout of the night, while the food left room for improvement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbyfOwno-7dGbncbtO9TSOrmb9DQ54aKS69iWH&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Johnson Hsin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJod1Ky8nWyo6bJwD11XbmtXok3a518fIFRBw8HjqKKYlhXqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time going to Bow & Stern since they've opened a few months ago. We went to happy hour at 2 pm for oyster, and the server told us they ran out before happy hour started. This was unfortunate, but we ended up getting two clam and mussels, honey chicken sliders, and the lobster grilled cheese sandwich. The sliders are decent, and the chicken was hot and breaded nicely. The mussels and the sauce were good. The clam came to us with lots of sand inside, and the cream sauce was over seasoned (very salty). We had to get this sent back, but the server was nice enough to get the kitchen to remake it. The second time we tried it, it would be a lot better and would recommend it. Lastly, the lobster grilled cheese.. decent amount of lobster inside, but the mozzarella was overpowering. Dont get me wrong, I love cheese, but it was like I was eating only cheese. The bread was toasted well, and the fries were good.

Overall experience was okay. I feel like the food really needs some work. The servers and ambiance of the place were great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm2nF1NI4sZyVrpP0ha1vUjG95RutHtk1KdqZg&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Ling To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlFxJCKp6bjqARUOXgwrUpHcbKAm9tBpTn_ze63uacIdbffw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We came for happy hour. A tad underwhelming since we were one of a handful of tables. Since the restaurant opened a little over two months, decor remains crisp and welcoming.

Food took longer to arrive than I had expected considering the place was mostly dead. Instead of tasting fresh and hot. It was lukewarm. The bread that came with the chowder had hard crust. The fries that accompanied our cod tasted like it sat out for awhile.

Our server was nice enough but wasn't pro-active to get us refills. When we wrapped up our meal - he was busy tending to other tables so we had to flag another server for the $110 bill.

Lots of areas to improve on to compete with Earls and Tap and Barrel where we typically go!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjivyJtoNdh6bW-PYiszugweEmPCz6x0aeBu_3&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Thomas Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUITuDRjw9J9Us45xAUXKSfp8lG2sJ2s04TW_lNAi_G6a5d62ur=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I enjoyed my visit to bow and stern very much. I had the chicken burger and was able to also taste the lobster poutine, and the calamari. Overall the food was tasty however I would not recommend the hot honey chicken burger as it was a bit dry. Other than that good experience. The staff were attentive and friendly and the restaurant looks very nice in terms of decorations and furniture. The value was okay but this is a nicer restaurant so higher prices are to be expected.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_Lygl4BJgK34ge0T4zXrVA_e1INrUM3oJxo0P&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Jay Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgJ3GqWqzz5gKwDw9Rk0BtDOxoj9fHklquopBItC7yPtZgIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Happy that they opened one in Brentwood! I really love the clam chowder here, has quite a bit of clams, right amount of kick and consistently good. Seafood tower was fresh and tasty. Lobster dip was also amazing. The service was quick, friendly and attentive. We'll definitely be back again! Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhyoTs60c-I1gtz31xzxCe8eiywpfq-xTL9WCF&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This kind of establishment has been long overdue in Burnaby, especially on the northern side. The location is spot-on, and we discovered it the old-fashioned way—not through an ad or review, but simply because it stood out from the street, towering above the neighboring structures. Inside, it’s spacious yet inviting, with an interior design that feels both grand and comfortable. The menu is extensive and diverse. Service was spot-on too. Wade took care of us and did a fantastic job, striking just the right balance between attentive and relaxed. The food itself? No complaints, as everything was beautifully balanced, leaving us fully satisfied. However, the experience wasn’t without its hiccups. Perhaps due to the sheer size of the place, the food arrived painfully slow, even the oysters. And they weren’t even at half capacity, from what I could tell. There seemed to be a bit of a bottleneck between the kitchen and the table, and I could actually watch my coffee sit at the bar long enough to go cold, which is a bit disappointing, especially given the impressive coffee setup they have. I’m hoping these are just teething issues as they figure things out because this place has serious potential. Despite the delays, we thoroughly enjoyed our lunch and are hopeful that they will iron out the kinks soon. Burnaby needs more spots like this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP03Uds5HCB7UR2cKiqKzstc_7kyrlRpZ0PA6He&fid=0x0:0x8937a4abaea624bb"],"When":"2024-10-2"}]

[{"Name":"natalie choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCDOGDe5AR7I6vCC6vXNkYAPGiiva_XFG1NK-SEZ23BDPzhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely not acceptable! Very disappointing!! I love Saboten in Richmond, I used to be there quite often. But this Saboten in Brentwood, I will never come back again. The Loin Katsu Don is SOAKED with the sauce, I can’t even finish half of the rice as it was way too sweet and salty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvrWVr9fANwBSJIj6orjzhmpoIm-FzZwCwy7h4&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"YVR Duke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbrjJ5U6gKw7Gn1zE_GlxhUndims9WHlh7sVaHLXVrjOFlYd_B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Dining in at Saboten offers an overall okay experience with satisfactory food quality. However, my recent takeout experience was disappointing. After dining in, I ordered a takeout meal for a family member.

Any professional fried food restaurant should know to poke holes in the container lid to let the moisture escape and keep the cutlet crispy. Unfortunately, despite Saboten's long-standing presence in Asia, they don't seem to care, resulting in a soggy cutlet by the time it reached home.

i shouldn’t leave any tips nor i will do any take out in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzK9_o2O51lxYIigf-zQp2lGnAf5aKliwhgURx&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Daniel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ_My_XXEDwRP-VKIxc7fFkIH3KYpWqXa9BUWbstP2f0vPF_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I noticed that the loin katsu has become much thinner than before. I hope they didn't cut the loin in half to make more money. The batter is also falling apart from the meat, which indicates that the quality of the food and the cooking skills need improvement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXAzn6qVFLqBu71BfekizO7cxe7oP73r8noD-h&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Caleb Millard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_XS8a5pAFnS6TBpIeToG_uctKcWiaDnG22VO-gePC23Ab0wCa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"An amazing little restaurant, the food was great, could use some salt in the curry itself otherwise great, the order I got said 2 piece katsu curry, but it only came with 1 so that was fairly disappointing. They did reach out to give me another dish to make up for it so that made my experience much much better. The rice was perfectly cooked and the pork katsu I had was also amazing, it is a good portion size for what you are paying for and for quality compared to other fast food places","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yasuyuki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5zOnHjrHZGUsGEA3Gk4TnCPhhRurUDrtZAvugdcbyXxDOiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was great !! My favorite is Loin Katsu Don. This is nice and tasty sauces, which is mixed together and it is perfect dishes. And also, it was smoothly served. Definitely, will back to order.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alejandra Sánchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXt051hy6gEMXkR86-3Xw80cqEx_9MawHfw61-PI0olAIeczxE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was good but the Katsu don rice had soooo much vinegar I couldn't finish it. The service was good but could be better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZPnczrPA8hqarvq0WfmVZzpHoE4KlTc9Wqwib&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Jamie L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIsaaODpzZi62wV-93lE__3OFGYxafaFgdJgxMDBfyIfS_ESBX0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered two dishes, one came out in reasonable time, the other came out 30 minutes after ordering.
Tenderllin katsu curry was good amd came out on time, but chicken katsu dong was the late one and on top of that, eggshells were found as we ate. Such an unpleasant experience! We should have checked the reviews before ordering from here. It was really expensive too. Two dishes came out to $37.28 while the food portion nor the quality was worth that much.
I used to like Saboten in other countries, but won't be coming back here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXSW_IoQaQ6B2hSlOXSeQZLvYxUoIaPKzonuUa&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"Jason D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV14HLbc6Ze7JZiJufUEhwiQ1I37e9rPxJ7pjEPsypNxuqatRs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Honestly the katsu is not too bad but the portions on the front display is misleading. You will get two or three slices worth of pork for $17.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXklvmzoGqJI2nJIef9mIJvtuexTtWHUgXw1s&fid=0x0:0x84c0fbbf5e199408"],"When":"2024-5-18"}]

[{"Name":"Whitney Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXWUpCHpQw9t28OfKhr7N_38-v3xiAMq2FEIM7zR2elX7xcEVO6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Picked up take out from Little Cockatoo Cafe. The pljeskavica here is pretty much an open faced burger with a meat patty that is well seasoned - the meat is so tender and juicy. I’m trying not to drool as I write this review. I also tried their cvari which is the Balkan version of pork rinds. I can’t comment on their ambience and restaurant decor but their food is definitely 11/10.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTouyOsLgIn2wjmYv7BAffM4ljLZ3ZKLWkUsqv&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2019-4-26"},{"Name":"Diego Aviles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLd1C9Gr5_19-RtFOj7Ylur0DHPT0rJrP-ewPHbv48LSZei6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a great hole in the wall. Owner and cook is very nice. One man show. Worth the wait for our food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYbssIv1GI6JFeRv2e-lnTe-e0NQiU-ya6a1fd&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2024-1-28"},{"Name":"Kelvin Fong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYlOJ0ZWKycRqx5ZOzHhnjusnD1vSd-Gno_8IQ4mNi6hmtCYtiSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious! Lots of meat. So if you are in the mood for grilled meats, beer, bread cheese and euro soccer, this is your place to visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOW9e_kF03RvU7b502gIJGlL7Yhp5yQJAw4BxTD&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2022-12-1"},{"Name":"charlie goff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAoLpdqWD8KtdupT8iXNWlndRPOdbArcOWpEZTbvkI76jV2hOO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Being from Texas and enjoying BBQ this was definitely a different but amazing experience! Great food and great service. There’s a reason they have such a good reviews.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnz9xq_Yap0kTdvGpdhDDr1jum4UpcWVCB90oS&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"Simon Bort","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuruoEPpIaCU8Iph5JQrlDL1FCejWX0z7Y-ZrpMfcbquA7xPMCSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let this amazing man seduce your taste buds. The sausages and meats are made by the grill master/owner himself. Everything we tried was super tasty. Good prices and portions.

More people should know about this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWfC_1cl63qYzDpvGvu3L7aRoNTq7zHi40do0v&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2022-8-11"},{"Name":"Sean C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKle1H3U_yb0rWRIsaUg4PFRlzNPbW3ErM52REVu0iehb-oMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The cevapcici (mixed pork and beef) served at Little Cockatoo are tender, juicy, and flavourful. The bread and kajmak which accompanied the cevaps were superior to those served at competing Southeastern European restaurants in Burnaby. This restaurant also offers all-beef cevapcici for those who don't eat pork, or simply prefer beef.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-6mym9Bykp1BIsMEnhoYRC3N9JUglDAHFmb-s&fid=0x0:0x1883fee644a6e217"],"When":"2023-2-28"},{"Name":"Sil Knezevic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmC1oMDgcJPYWexS2hvVeWfMHffqzyTfXmne5kYixFylhsyYtp2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place exceeded all my expectations. If I could give them 6 stars I would. We ordered a meat platter, and 6 sides. My goodness, it was like being teleported back to grandma's house. The meats were juicy and packed with flavour. The sides were all perfectly balanced and the salads were fresh and vibrant.
The ordering process was quick and simple, the owner is a pleasure to speak with! I wish I had known of this place earlier as I believe it's the best Balkan food around. Do yourself a favour and try it out!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Edmond Kan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhs8-Bq6r9RXlToNM1Zb4RaXApUjRArZ6BuqgjWMteHJSBo252=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is not your normal restaurant. This is more like a casual hangout cafe. Walked in to order because I couldn't find a menu online. 0rdered the platter for one and sausage, it was more than enough for 2 people. Platter comes with lots of different favorful meats served with rice and grilled veggies. Try it! Call ahead to pickup!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"DG EG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8BZ5fVc2OhL9EZwFliQV3aWbnsm2S7LB1ItAUcgbC8-Kozw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Great service up until about a year ago. Never had a problem with Freshly Roast Coffee but was shocked at their lack of customer service. They stopped changing the filters on the water cooler or coffee machine, last change was prior to 2020, and recently without discussion they removed equipment and wouldn’t offer a refund on unopened product. Would not recommend using them for your office coffee needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Willetta Les","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX22hIrDvFrQei1us7-7R5uNoH6EKsSMd-b8BncEyDMejhpTxo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have had two coffee machines and two filtered water coolers through Freshly Roasted Coffee Co since November 2015.  Their service has been absolutely incredible.  We could not ask for more.

Very quick response to the very few problems we've had, random check-ins to see how everything is going/clean the machines,  and easy to order supplies with next day delivery.

We really appreciate their great communication with us and that they're willing to provide wonderful service to us, being that we are in Chilliwack - far from their typical service hub.

After working with a couple different companies/machines, we are so very happy to have found Freshly Roasted Coffee Co.
And everyone LOVES the on-demand fresh coffee with lots of options :)

Cheers to an excellent company to work with.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Garry Dhillon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLC-syxjEKb06rQsNQOBhR7Gj3jYjIvyawrBtYn0ZETVUb_A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great company to deal with.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nanaimo Mitsubishi Receptionist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqrNRmp6UzG84gK6NlDlC__wtPu1t8YlmodsdSW074ZpWzrmXh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Reyad Bazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOigQTX6waNFJSewWaEzrcVPJAF9x0PnKwUdoV3Q_CKfagA30=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""}]
